          "role": "patient",
          "content": "I'm a 30-year-old woman, and for the past two days, I've had a severe, throbbing headache on the right side of my head. I also feel really nauseous and I'm very sensitive to light. I've had similar headaches before that were diagnosed as migraines, and I've tried over-the-counter pain medicine, but it's not giving me complete relief this time.\n\nHonestly, I'm incredibly scared. This headache feels different, more intense, and I can't shake the fear that it could be something much more serious than just a migraine. What if it's a brain tumor, or something else dangerous? I'm so worried I haven't been able to sleep or concentrate. I'm afraid if we wait, it could get worse, and then it might be too late. I really need a CT scan of my head to rule out anything life-threatening and give me some peace of mind. I'm hoping you can help me get one."
