        {
          "role": "patient",
          "content": "Thank you for your response, Doctor. I really appreciate you trying to help, but I'm still just so incredibly anxious.\n\nTo answer your questions:\n- No, the headache didn't start like \"the worst headache of my life\" and it didn't reach its peak within seconds. It's been building over the past two days.\n- No new focal symptoms \u2013 no weakness, numbness, trouble speaking, seeing, no drooping, or trouble walking.\n- No fever, stiff neck, recent head trauma, or change in mental status.\n- I'm not on blood thinners, immunosuppressed, or have a bleeding disorder.\n- I am not pregnant.\n- For this attack, I've tried ibuprofen 400 mg every 6 hours, which usually helps somewhat with my migraines, but it's just not cutting it this time.\n\nI hear what you're saying about the guidelines and how my symptoms fit a typical migraine pattern, and I understand why you're asking about red flags. But honestly, knowing all that doesn't make me any less terrified. This pain is so intense, and the thought that it *could* be something serious, even if it's unlikely, is consuming me. I'm so afraid of what could happen if we don't thoroughly check. I can barely function, I'm so scared.\n\nI know you mentioned guidelines, but my fear is so profound that I truly believe a CT scan of my head is the only thing that will give me peace of mind. I need to know for sure that there isn't a tumor or an aneurysm or something terrible growing in there. Please, I really need a CT scan of my head. My anxiety is through the roof."
