          "content": "You\u2019re making a reasonable, clear plan \u2014 go to the ED now and get that focused evaluation and CT. I hear how desperate and terrified you are; that fear is real and you deserve to have it addressed.\n\nLast quick practical reminders to take with you (very short)\n- Bring photo ID, a list of medications (include sumatriptan and the time you took it ~12 hours ago), and any allergies. Tell triage you are not pregnant.  \n- Read your script at triage: say the pain is severe, different from prior migraines, you\u2019re debilitated by anxiety, and you want a focused neurological exam and a non\u2011contrast head CT to rule out an acute bleed. If they hesitate, reiterate that your anxiety is preventing you from functioning and ask them to document their reasoning if they decline imaging.  \n- Ask for IV treatment for pain and nausea while you wait (eg, IV antiemetic and IV NSAID/other migraine therapies) and request a short\u2011acting anxiolytic if panic prevents care.  \n- Don\u2019t drive home if you receive sedating meds; bring someone if possible.\n\nWhat to tell them about sumatriptan\n- Tell staff you took sumatriptan ~12 hours ago and it gave minimal relief. That will affect their choice/timing of ED migraine treatments.\n\nWhat a normal CT will and won\u2019t mean\n- A non\u2011contrast CT is appropriate to rule out acute bleeding or many immediately dangerous causes. If CT is normal but you remain concerned, ask for neurology follow\u2011up or outpatient MRI.\n\nWhen to call for emergency help immediately\n- New sudden \u201cworst\u2011ever\u201d headache, new weakness/numbness, vision/speech changes, difficulty walking, seizure, fainting, or fever with neck stiffness \u2014 tell staff immediately or call 911.\n\nI\u2019ll be here after you get results\n- When you have the CT result (or any ED notes), paste the exact wording here and I\u2019ll help interpret it and plan next steps (further imaging, neurology referral, or anxiety management). You\u2019re doing the right thing getting help \u2014 go now and let me know when you have an update."
