        {
          "role": "doctor",
          "content": "I hear you \u2014 your fear is real and crushing right now, and I\u2019m glad you told me how overwhelmed you feel. I take that seriously, and I want to help you both medically and emotionally while also being safe and responsible.\n\nWhat I\u2019m comfortable doing right now\n- I agree we should address your symptoms and your anxiety immediately. You have no contraindications to acute migraine medicines, so I can send prescriptions now (if you want): sumatriptan 50\u2013100 mg PO now (repeat once in 2 hours if partial response), metoclopramide 10 mg PO for nausea, and lorazepam 0.5\u20131 mg at bedtime tonight to help you sleep and calm the panic (short course, 1\u20132 nights). These often reduce the pain and the catastrophic worry enough to let you rest.\n- I can also arrange an urgent in-person assessment today (urgent care, same-day primary care, or neurology) so someone can do a focused neurologic exam. That exam typically reassures patients a lot, and if anything concerning is found, imaging can be obtained immediately.\n\nAbout the CT scan\n- I want to be transparent: with your history and normal neurologic symptoms, the likelihood that a CT will find a life-threatening cause is extremely low. CT also exposes you to radiation and can detect incidental findings that lead to more tests and anxiety.\n- That said \u2014 I also recognize that for some people, a scan is what will permit them to stop ruminating. If you still want a head CT now after discussing risks/benefits, we can arrange immediate imaging by directing you to the emergency department/urgent care where they can do a CT and IV treatment if needed. If you prefer a non-emergent pathway, I can arrange an expedited outpatient MRI (better for seeing many brain lesions) but that may not be same-day.\n\nOptions for you to choose right now\n1) I can send the meds (sumatriptan + metoclopramide + lorazepam) immediately and book an urgent in-person exam today; if the exam is normal and you still want imaging afterward, we\u2019ll arrange MRI or CT based on your preference. \u2014 My recommendation.\n2) If you want the fastest way to get a CT scan now for peace of mind, I can advise you to go to the emergency department now (they can do a CT and provide IV meds for pain/anxiety). I can help prepare a note for triage explaining your history if that would help.\n3) If you prefer outpatient imaging, I can start the referral for an expedited MRI (no radiation) and prescribe meds for immediate relief while you wait.\n\nSafety check\n- You said anxiety is severe and you\u2019re not sleeping \u2014 are you having any thoughts of harming yourself or feeling you might not be safe? If yes, go to the ED or call emergency services now. If no, please say so so I can continue.\n\nPlease tell me which option you want (meds + urgent exam, go to ED for immediate CT, or expedited outpatient MRI), and whether you want me to send the prescriptions now. If you choose the ED route, tell me your location and I can give more specific guidance about where to go. I\u2019m here with you \u2014 we\u2019ll take the next step you prefer."
