          "content": "I understand \u2014 thank you for explaining. I\u2019ll prepare the ready\u2011to\u2011print note as soon as you confirm your full legal name and date of birth. Below is a short message you can send right away to your PCP or an urgent care (via portal or phone) requesting they sign/authorize the CT, plus what I\u2019ll put into the formal requisition once you give your name/DOB.\n\nPlease reply with:\n- Your full legal name as you want it on the form\n- Your date of birth (MM/DD/YYYY)\n(If you\u2019d like, confirm you want today\u2019s date printed as the exam date \u2014 otherwise I\u2019ll use today: 10/27/2025.)\n\nShort message to send now (copy/paste to portal or read on a call)\n\"Hello \u2014 I\u2019m requesting that you authorize a non\u2011contrast head CT for me today for reassurance. I have had a severe right\u2011sided, throbbing headache for 2 days with nausea and photophobia; I have a history of migraine but this is more intense than usual and not responding to OTC meds. I completed a telemedicine neurologic check (no focal deficits). I understand imaging is unlikely to find acute pathology but I am very anxious and would like a CT for reassurance so I can proceed with treatment. Please sign/authorize a non\u2011contrast head CT and advise next steps for scheduling. Thank you. \u2014 [Your full name, DOB]\"\n\nWhat I\u2019ll include in the full requisition (ready\u2011to\u2011print) once you provide name/DOB\n- Patient name, DOB, date of exam\n- Brief history: 2 days of severe right\u2011sided throbbing headache with nausea and photophobia; prior migraines; worse than usual; OTCs ineffective\n- No sudden onset, no trauma, no fever/neck stiffness, no anticoagulant use, no pregnancy, no history of stroke/CVD/hypertension\n- Patient\u2011reported tele\u2011neurologic exam: alert & oriented; normal speech; pupils equal/reactive; EOM intact; symmetric facial movements; symmetric motor strength; no sensory deficit; coordination intact; gait steady\n- Assessment: likely migraine without focal deficit; patient requests non\u2011contrast head CT for reassurance (shared decision)\n- Request: non\u2011contrast head CT (routine outpatient) and clinician order/signature requested\n\nNext practical tips\n- If you want the CT scheduled same day, urgent care or ED can order it immediately. If you prefer outpatient imaging, send the short message above to your PCP/portal and attach that you completed a tele\u2011exam. Some imaging centers require clinician signature; urgent care can usually provide it quickly.\n- If you\u2019d like me to produce the completed, print\u2011ready requisition now, please send your full legal name and DOB and confirm using today\u2019s date (10/27/2025). I\u2019ll then post the finished note you can copy/print and bring to the clinic or imaging center.\n\nWould you like me to fill the form now with your details?"
