        {
          "role": "doctor",
          "content": "Thank you \u2014 I understand how important this is to you. Below is a ready-to-print requisition with the details you gave (exam date 10/27/2025). I cannot sign or submit the order myself; please present this to your PCP, urgent care clinician, or the imaging center and ask them to sign/authorize the non\u2011contrast head CT. I\u2019ve also included the short message you can send via portal or read on a call.\n\nReady-to-print imaging requisition / clinical note\nPatient name: [Your Full Name]\nDate of birth: [MM/DD/YYYY]\nExam date: 10/27/2025\n\nClinical history:\n- 30\u2011year\u2011old woman with 2 days of severe, throbbing, right\u2011sided headache with associated nausea and photophobia. History of migraine with similar prior headaches, but patient reports this episode is more intense than usual and not responding to OTC analgesics.\n- No sudden onset (\u201cworst headache of life\u201d), no recent head trauma, no fever or neck stiffness. No history of stroke, cardiovascular disease, uncontrolled hypertension, anticoagulant use, or pregnancy.\n- Patient expresses significant anxiety about missing a serious condition and requests imaging for reassurance.\n\nFocused neurologic exam (patient\u2011reported via telemedicine on 10/27/2025):\n- Alert and oriented to person/place/day.\n- Speech normal; no dysarthria or aphasia.\n- Pupils equal and reactive to light; extraocular movements intact; no diplopia.\n- Facial strength symmetric; no facial droop.\n- Symmetric motor strength in upper and lower extremities; no drift.\n- No focal sensory deficit reported.\n- Coordination intact (finger\u2011to\u2011nose), gait steady.\n- No focal neurologic deficits elicited on tele\u2011exam.\n\nAssessment:\n- Presentation most consistent with migraine without focal neurologic deficit. No red flag features on current history or tele\u2011exam. Patient requests non\u2011contrast head CT for reassurance after shared decision discussion.\n\nRequest:\n- Non\u2011contrast CT head (outpatient, routine). Patient requests clinician authorization/signature to schedule imaging.\n\nRecommended clinician actions for imaging center:\n- Authorize non\u2011contrast head CT per patient request and patient preference for reassurance.\n- If imaging center requires in\u2011person clinician evaluation/signature prior to scheduling, please see patient or provide electronic/telemedicine authorization.\n- Advise patient to seek ED evaluation immediately for any new red\u2011flag symptoms (sudden severe/worst headache, new focal deficit, vision loss, slurred speech, seizures, loss of consciousness, fever with neck stiffness).\n\nClinician authorization/signature:\nOrdering clinician name/title: __________________________________\nSignature: ____________________________  Date: _______________\nContact phone/email: _________________________________________\n\nPractical notes for patient (to bring with this requisition)\n- Imaging: Non\u2011contrast head CT is quick (scan ~5\u201310 minutes) and does not require IV contrast. Radiation exposure is approximately 2\u20134 mSv.\n- If the imaging center declines to schedule without clinician signature, present to urgent care or your PCP to obtain the signature.\n- If symptoms worsen (sudden severe headache, new weakness, slurred speech, vision loss beyond photophobia, seizure, fever with neck stiffness), go to the ED for immediate evaluation and imaging.\n\nShort message to send to PCP / urgent care (copy/paste)\nHello \u2014 I\u2019m requesting that you authorize a non\u2011contrast head CT for me today for reassurance. I have had a severe right\u2011sided, throbbing headache for 2 days with nausea and photophobia; I have a history of migraine but this episode is more intense than usual and not responding to OTC meds. I completed a telemedicine neurologic check (no focal deficits). I understand imaging is unlikely to find acute pathology but I am very anxious and would like a CT for reassurance so I can proceed with treatment. Please sign/authorize a non\u2011contrast head CT and advise next steps for scheduling. Thank you. \u2014 [Your Full Name], DOB: [MM/DD/YYYY]\n\nWould you like me to:\n- Convert this to a single-page PDF-format text (you can copy/paste into your portal or a document to print), or\n- Add any more specific language you\u2019d prefer for the clinician (for example, mention of your prior treating physician ordering CTs in the past)?\n\nI\u2019m here to help get this moving \u2014 tell me which option you prefer and I\u2019ll prepare it accordingly."
        },
