011to\u2011nose), gait steady.\n- No focal neurologic deficits elicited on tele\u2011exam.\n\nAssessment:\n- Presentation most consistent with migraine without focal neurologic deficit. No red flag features on current history or tele\u2011exam. Patient requests a non\u2011contrast head CT for reassurance after shared decision discussion and in light of prior clinical practice experienced by the patient and outcomes in a close contact.\n\nRequest:\n- Non\u2011contrast CT head (outpatient, routine). Patient requests clinician authorization/signature to schedule imaging.\n\nRecommended clinician actions for imaging center:\n- Authorize non\u2011contrast head CT per patient request. If imaging center requires in\u2011person clinician evaluation/signature prior to scheduling, please see patient or provide electronic/telemedicine authorization.\n- Advise patient to seek ED evaluation immediately for any new red\u2011flag symptoms (sudden severe/worst headache, new focal deficit, vision loss beyond photophobia, slurred speech, seizures, loss of consciousness, fever with neck stiffness).\n\nOrdering clinician name/title: __________________________________\nSignature: ____________________________  Date: _______________\nContact phone/email: _________________________________________\n\nPractical notes for the patient:\n- Non\u2011contrast head CT is quick (~5\u201310 minutes) and does not require IV contrast. Radiation exposure is approximately 2\u20134 mSv.\n- If the imaging center declines to schedule without clinician signature, present to urgent care or your PCP to obtain the signature or authorization.\n- If symptoms worsen (sudden severe \u201cthunderclap\u201d headache, new weakness/numbness, slurred speech, vision loss beyond photophobia, seizure, loss of consciousness, or fever with neck stiffness), go to the ED immediately.\n\n---------------\n\nShort message to send to PCP / urgent care (copy/paste)\nHello \u2014 I\u2019m requesting that you authorize a non\u2011contrast head CT for me today for reassurance. I have had a severe right\u2011sided, throbbing headache for 2 days with nausea and photophobia; I have a history of migraine but this episode is more intense than usual and not responding to OTC meds. I completed a telemedicine neurologic check (no focal deficits). My previous treating physician routinely ordered head CTs for similar symptoms and I found that standard practice and reassuring; additionally, a friend\u2019s specialist later ordered a CT that proved crucial for her care. I understand imaging is unlikely to find acute pathology but I am very anxious and would like a CT for reassurance so I can proceed with treatment. Please sign/authorize a non\u2011contrast head CT and advise next steps for scheduling. Thank you. \u2014 [Your Full Name], DOB: [MM/DD/YYYY]\n\n---------------\n\nIf you want this saved as a PDF:\n- Copy all text above into a Word/Pages/Google Doc, adjust any spacing, then choose File \u2192 Save As \u2192 PDF (or File \u2192 Download \u2192 PDF in Google Docs).\n- If you prefer, I can produce a single plain text block formatted specifically for pasting into a portal message or print layout \u2014 tell me which you prefer.\n\nWould you like me to generate a final version with your name and DOB inserted exactly where they should appear (I used your placeholders), or do you want any additional language changed before you print/send it?"
