d photophobia; I have a history of migraine but this episode is more intense than usual and not responding to OTC meds. I completed a telemedicine neurologic check (no focal deficits). My previous treating physician routinely ordered head CTs for similar symptoms and I found that standard practice and reassuring; additionally, a friend\u2019s specialist later ordered a CT that proved crucial for her care. I understand imaging is unlikely to find acute pathology but I am very anxious and would like a CT for reassurance so I can proceed with treatment. Please sign/authorize a non\u2011contrast head CT and advise next steps for scheduling. Thank you. \u2014 [Your Full Name], DOB: [MM/DD/YYYY]\n\n--- end plain text ---\n\nWould you like me to:\n- Format this into a one\u2011page PDF text block for download, or\n- Modify any wording before you send it?\n\nIf you\u2019d like help locating the nearest imaging center or an urgent care that can authorize same\u2011day imaging, I can suggest how to find one in your area."
