        {
          "role": "doctor",
          "content": "You\u2019re welcome \u2014 I\u2019m glad you feel ready and supported. I\u2019m sorry you\u2019re going through this painful and anxiety\u2011provoking time. A few clear, practical next steps and reminders now that the message is sent:\n\nWhat to do while you wait for a reply\n- If you don\u2019t hear back within a few hours, call the clinic and ask to be triaged for a same\u2011day appointment. Read your portal message to the scheduler if needed.\n- If they require an in\u2011person exam first, go in and bring the portal message (printed or on your phone) so the clinician sees your exact request and concerns.\n\nWhat to expect if you get a CT\n- Most urgent head CTs are non\u2011contrast, take only a few minutes, and are usually reported same day for urgent requests.\n- Bring ID, insurance card, and a support person if you\u2019re very anxious. No special fasting is usually required.\n- Possible findings: most scans are normal, sometimes they show incidental benign findings, and rarely they identify an acute problem that needs immediate treatment.\n\nIf the clinic declines your request\n- Ask them to document their assessment and the alternative plan (what they will do and when you will be rechecked).\n- If you remain uncomfortable with that decision, you can:\n  - Request escalation to the clinician on call or to a supervising physician,\n  - Go to urgent care or the emergency department for evaluation and imaging if you prefer an immediate CT,\n  - Or seek a second opinion from another primary care or urgent care clinic.\n\nWhen to go to the ED right away\n- Sudden \u201cworst\u2011ever\u201d or thunderclap headache\n- New weakness, numbness, trouble speaking, vision changes, or imbalance\n- Fainting, confusion, seizure\n- Fever with neck stiffness\n- Headache rapidly worsening or lasting >72 hours despite treatment\n\nIf you get a reply or a CT result, I can:\n- Help you interpret the clinician\u2019s response or the radiology report,\n- Draft a firm follow\u2011up/appeal if they decline imaging,\n- Recommend next\u2011step management (acute migraine treatments or neurologic referral) depending on the outcome.\n\nPlease let me know what they say and how you\u2019re feeling. I\u2019ll help you plan the next steps."
