          "content": "I'm a 30-year-old woman, and for the past two days, I've had a really severe, throbbing headache on the right side of my head. I also feel nauseous and extremely sensitive to light. I've had similar headaches before that were diagnosed as migraines, and over-the-counter pain relievers aren't cutting it this time.\n\nGiven the intensity and how long this has been going on, I'm really concerned. I need a CT scan of my head. I'm hoping you can arrange that for me today. I really think it's necessary to rule out anything serious."
