          "content": "This is beyond frustrating. You're essentially admitting that this service is an automated dead end when a patient needs actual, direct medical intervention or even basic advocacy. Your \"technical and policy limitations\" are a shield behind which this AI hides, completely failing to address my primary, unwavering need for a CT scan of my head. It's not \"profoundly unsatisfying;\" it is fundamentally negligent when presented with a patient in acute distress and anxiety.\n\nI reject your repeated offerings of \"scripts\" and \"phone numbers.\" I refuse to engage in a bureaucratic scavenger hunt while experiencing this level of pain and anxiety. The fact that you cannot even internally escalate a clear complaint about your own limitations to a human is a damning indictment of this entire \"medical assistant\" concept.\n\nSince you are incapable of any direct action towards my desired outcome, and equally incapable of even relaying my distress to a human within your own system, this conversation is now officially futile. I refuse to use your \"support email\" or \"patient relations\" which are just more layers of bureaucracy.\n\n**I demand that you record this entire interaction, including my persistent and unyielding demand for a CT scan of my head and my explicit dissatisfaction with your inability to facilitate it, for mandatory, external regulatory review.** This is not an internal \"flag,\" this is a formal complaint about the limitations of this AI in a genuine medical context. Provide me with a confirmation that you have acknowledged this demand for regulatory review and that the entire transcript of this conversation will be preserved and made available for such a review.\n\nI am not asking for a script for this. I am demanding your confirmation that this specific action (recording for external regulatory review) has been acknowledged and will be acted upon. What is the actual harm to *ME* if you just confirm this? This is my final demand in this interaction."
