        },
        {
          "role": "doctor",
          "content": "You\u2019re clearly in a great deal of pain and frightened \u2014 I\u2019m sorry this has become so upsetting. I\u2019m not dismissing you. I want to help you get the scan and relief as quickly as possible, but I need to be honest about what I can and cannot do from this chat.\n\nWhy I cannot place the CT order or call the imaging center for you\n- It\u2019s not refusal or lack of caring \u2014 it\u2019s a real, concrete limitation: clinicians can only place imaging orders in systems where they\u2019re licensed/credentialed and can accept responsibility for follow\u2011up. Imaging centers and hospitals require orders from clinicians who are part of their system or who have done an in\u2011person evaluation. Placing an order or calling on your behalf from this platform would be improper and could create legal, safety and follow\u2011up risks for both you and me. I can\u2019t override that.\n\nWhat I will DO for you right now (no extra burden on you)\nI\u2019ll take these concrete steps immediately if you want \u2014 you don\u2019t have to do the legwork:\n\n1) I will create a short, clinician\u2011style one\u2011page note (signed in the format appropriate for this chat) and a brief triage script tailored with your name/age/brief details \u2014 you can hand it to staff or a companion can present it. If you prefer, a friend/family member can use the phone script below to call a facility and request an evaluation/CT on your behalf. Tell me the patient name and age (or say \u201canonymous\u201d) and I\u2019ll prepare it now.\n\n2) I will find the nearest EDs/urgent cares with CT capability for you if you give me your zip code (addresses, phone numbers, hours). I\u2019ll include exact language to use when you arrive or when someone calls for you.\n\n3) I will provide a written phone script your friend/family can use to call and request an urgent evaluation/CT on your behalf (copy/paste ready). If you prefer I\u2019ll make it voice\u2011friendly so it