lie in a dark, quiet room, cold compress, sip fluids.\n- If pills won\u2019t stay down or oral meds fail, go to ED for IV antiemetic and IV migraine rescue (which often works quickly).\n\nWhen to go to the ED immediately\n- Sudden \u201cthunderclap\u201d headache (reaches peak intensity within seconds/minutes).\n- New weakness, numbness, slurred speech, vision loss, confusion, seizure, fever with stiff neck, fainting, or altered consciousness.\n- Inability to control pain/vomiting at home despite the rescue meds, or continuous severe headache >72 hours.\n\nIf you want, I will:\n- Stay with you to walk through taking the medications and what to expect.\n- Write a very brief one\u2011line statement you can say to ED/urgent care staff to make your request clear and direct.\n- Help you decide whether to go to ED now or try meds at home.\n\nYou are not being dismissed. I can\u2019t place the order, but I will do everything I can in this chat to get you the testing and relief you want as quickly as possible. Do you want to try the rescue meds now or head to the ED for immediate imaging and IV treatment?"
