          "content": "You\u2019re welcome \u2014 I\u2019m glad the scripts are helpful. Safe trip to the ED. A few quick reminders before you go:\n\n- Bring photo ID, insurance card, a list of current medications and allergies, and any prior imaging reports/CDs if you have them (they can be very helpful).  \n- Be prepared for a urine pregnancy test (EDs routinely do this for CT in people of childbearing potential).  \n- Ask triage to note that you want urgent evaluation, IV antiemetic/analgesic for symptom relief, and that you\u2019d like a non\u2011contrast head CT for reassurance after the clinician\u2019s assessment (use the scripts you saved).  \n- If you feel too unwell to drive, consider having someone drive you or call emergency services. If you develop new neurologic signs (weakness, numbness, trouble speaking, sudden vision change), a sudden \u201cworst-ever\u201d headache, seizure, fainting, or fever with neck stiffness on the way, call 911 or go immediately to triage.\n\nIf you want, message me after your ED visit and I can help interpret the results, explain the discharge plan, or suggest follow\u2011up care. Take care \u2014 I hope you get relief and reassurance soon."
