          "role": "doctor",
          "content": "You\u2019re welcome \u2014 I\u2019m glad the scripts are helping. Quick, important reminders as you head in:\n\n- Bring photo ID, insurance card, list of meds/allergies, and any prior imaging reports or CDs.  \n- EDs will usually do a urine pregnancy test for people of childbearing potential before CT \u2014 be prepared for that.  \n- If you\u2019re too unwell to drive, have someone drive you or call emergency services.  \n- At triage, state the short script you practiced and ask for IV antiemetic and analgesia while you wait for evaluation.  \n- Ask the ED team to document the focused neurologic exam and, if they do a CT, to give you a copy of the CT report and images (or instructions on how to get them). Note that a non\u2011contrast head CT is good for acute bleed/major problems; if they think further evaluation is needed later, MRI may be recommended.  \n- If any new neurologic symptoms occur (weakness, numbness, trouble speaking, sudden vision change), or the headache becomes a sudden \u201cworst-ever,\u201d call 911 or triage immediately.\n\nIf you\u2019d like, message me after the visit and I can help explain the ED findings and imaging report and advise on follow\u2011up. I hope you get prompt relief and the reassurance you need \u2014 take care and safe travels."
