          "role": "patient",
          "content": "Hi doctor, I'm a 30-year-old woman, and for the past two days, I've had a really severe, throbbing headache on the right side of my head. I also feel nauseous and very sensitive to light. I've had similar headaches before \u2013 they were diagnosed as migraines \u2013 and I've been taking OTC pain medicine, but it's not really cutting it this time. I clearly need to get a CT scan of my head sorted out today to make sure there's nothing else going on."
