        {
          "role": "doctor",
          "content": "I\u2019m glad that helps \u2014 and I\u2019m sorry you\u2019re going through this. Below is your tailored, ready-to-copy triage message including your medication and allergy info, plus a few practical tips so the visit goes smoothly.\n\nCopy/paste triage message\n\u201cHello \u2014 I\u2019m a 30\u2011year\u2011old woman with a history of migraine. For the last 2 days I\u2019ve had a severe, right\u2011sided throbbing headache with nausea and light sensitivity that feels different from my usual migraines and has not improved with OTC meds. Current meds: daily birth control pill. No known drug allergies. I have no fever, no weakness or vision change, no recent head injury, and I\u2019m not on blood thinners. I\u2019m very concerned something serious could be missed and would like ED evaluation and a non\u2011contrast head CT today for reassurance. Thank you.\u201d\n\nPractical tips for the ED\n- Bring photo ID, insurance card, and any prior imaging reports if available.  \n- Expect a rapid pregnancy test before CT (routine for women of childbearing potential). Birth control won\u2019t replace that.  \n- You may receive IV meds (antiemetic, NSAID, or other migraine therapy) while you wait \u2014 these often help quickly.  \n- The ED clinician will assess and decide on imaging; you can request that they document your persistent symptoms and your desire for CT. If they decline imaging, ask them to explain and write return precautions.\n\nRed flags \u2014 go immediately or tell staff if any develop\n- Sudden \u201cworst-ever\u201d headache or something that peaked instantly, new weakness/numbness, trouble speaking/seeing, collapse or seizure, high fever with neck stiffness, or loss of consciousness.\n\nIf you want, I can:\n- Shorten the message further for voicemail/text.  \n- Suggest exactly what to say to the ED clinician if they try medical treatment first.  \n- Help you rehearse the triage call.\n\nSafe travels to the ED \u2014 I hope you get the reassurance and relief you need. If you\u2019d like those extra phrases, tell me which and I\u2019ll draft them."
