        {
          "role": "doctor",
          "content": "Below is a concise, clinician\u2011style outpatient order you can copy and bring to your PCP, urgent care, or imaging center. Fill in the patient identifiers and the ordering clinician details as needed.\n\nOrder: Non\u2011contrast CT head (outpatient, ASAP)\n\nClinical indication: 30\u2011year\u2011old female with severe, persistent, right\u2011sided throbbing headache for 48 hours with associated nausea and photophobia. History of prior migraine headaches with similar features. Symptoms have not responded to OTC analgesics. No focal neurologic deficits reported on review (no weakness, numbness, speech disturbance), no sudden thunderclap onset, no fever, no neck stiffness, and no seizures. Patient requests neuroimaging for reassurance given severity and persistence of pain.\n\nRequested study: Non\u2011contrast CT head to evaluate for acute intracranial process (e.g., hemorrhage, mass effect) per patient request.\n\nUrgency: Outpatient \u2014 earliest available appointment. Patient is willing to wait for scheduled imaging. If new focal neurologic signs, sudden severe worsening, fever/neck stiffness, or inability to tolerate oral intake occur, recommend ED evaluation for urgent imaging.\n\nSuggested ICD\u201110: R51 (Headache); G43.909 (Migraine, unspecified, without status migrainosus)\n\nPlease forward final report and any acute/urgent findings to the ordering clinician.\n\nOrdering clinician: _______________________  \nNPI: _________________ Phone: _________________ Fax: _________________  \nDate: ______________\n\nIf you want, I can tailor this to a specific clinic or add/send it in a format for your PCP \u2014 tell me the recipient and I\u2019ll adapt it. I\u2019m sorry this is so distressing; I hope the scan gives you the reassurance you need."
