          "content": "You\u2019re welcome \u2014 I\u2019m glad that helps. I\u2019m sorry you\u2019re dealing with such a bad headache. A few brief practical notes before you go:\n\n- Bring the printed order, photo ID, insurance card (if used), and a current medication list to the imaging center or clinic.  \n- Non\u2011contrast CT of the head is quick (minutes) and does not require fasting or special prep.  \n- If you develop any red\u2011flag symptoms before the scan \u2014 sudden \u201cworst\u2011ever\u201d headache, new weakness/numbness, trouble speaking, vision loss, fever with neck stiffness, seizures, or inability to keep liquids/meds down \u2014 go to the emergency department immediately for urgent imaging.  \n- After the scan, bring the report/images to your PCP or the clinician who ordered it; if you\u2019d like, you can share the report here and I can help explain the findings and next steps.\n\nPlease let me know if you want the order tailored to a specific clinic or need help drafting a message to your PCP. Wishing you some relief and reassurance soon \u2014 take care."
