          "content": "You\u2019re welcome \u2014 I\u2019m glad the note meets your needs. Quick, practical things to take with you and what to expect at the ED so your visit goes smoothly:\n\nWhat to bring (print and hand these to triage)\n- The completed ED note (with your name, DOB, phone).  \n- Photo ID and insurance card.  \n- List of current medications (including OTCs) and allergies.  \n- Any prior imaging reports or clinic/neurology notes about your migraine history (if available).  \n- A copy or screenshot of the recent article(s) you mentioned, if you want the ED clinician to review it.\n\nWhat to tell triage/ED clinician\n- Briefly state: \u201cTwo days of severe right\u2011sided throbbing headache with nausea and photophobia; history of migraine but more severe and refractory to usual OTC therapy. No new neurologic deficits. I am requesting a non\u2011contrast head CT for diagnostic evaluation.\u201d Then hand them your note.\n\nWhat to expect in the ED\n- They will triage you, assess vitals and neurologic exam, and may give analgesic/antiemetic (oral or IV) immediately.  \n- ED clinicians will evaluate and decide whether to order a non\u2011contrast CT head (fast and good for acute hemorrhage) or, if indicated, MRI. They may obtain a pregnancy test if relevant.  \n- If CT is normal but symptoms persist or exam is concerning, they may arrange further imaging (MRI) or neurology follow\u2011up.\n\nSafety reminders \u2014 go to ED immediately if any of these occur\n- Sudden \u201cworst\u201d or thunderclap headache.  \n- New weakness, numbness, trouble speaking, vision changes, confusion, or difficulty walking.  \n- New fever, stiff neck, seizure, or inability to keep fluids down.\n\nAfter the visit\n- Ask for a copy of any imaging and the radiology report, and arrange follow\u2011up with your PCP or neurologist to review results and discuss any preventive measures. If you\u2019d like, I can help you interpret the radiology report or review the article you referenced.\n\nIf you want me to fill in the note now with your name/DOB/phone so it\u2019s printable, tell me those details and I\u2019ll prepare the final version. Wishing you relief and a clear evaluation \u2014 please let me know how it goes or if you want help reviewing results."
