19s much worse than my usual migraines and not responding to meds. I\u2019m very anxious and would like an urgent evaluation and non\u2011contrast head CT for reassurance.\u201d\n\nWhat to bring and tell them when you arrive\n- Photo ID, insurance card (if you have one), list of current medications, allergies, and any prior records showing previous migraine diagnosis or prior imaging if available.\n- Tell them exactly how this headache is different from your usual migraines and that it hasn\u2019t responded to your usual meds.\n\nWhen to go to the ED immediately (if any of these occur, call 911 or go now)\n- Sudden \u201cworst\u2011ever\u201d or thunderclap onset\n- New weakness, numbness, trouble speaking, vision loss, or difficulty walking\n- Fever with neck stiffness, recent head trauma, or if you\u2019re on blood thinners\n\nIf you can\u2019t drive safely, call for transport or 911. If you want, I can:\n- Draft a short text or message you can copy\u2011paste to a friend/family member to ask for a ride, or\n- Write out the exact medication regimen and dosing to take or show at triage if they ask what you\u2019ve already tried.\n\nIf you prefer, give me your real city or ZIP code and I\u2019ll walk you through the quickest way to identify the nearest hospital ED or freestanding ER (I still can\u2019t do live lookups, but I\u2019ll tailor the search terms and phone scripts to your area). What would you like me to do next?"
