        {
          "role": "doctor",
          "content": "I\u2019m really sorry you\u2019re in so much pain and feeling so scared \u2014 that must be awful. I hear you clearly: you want a concrete list of nearby EDs/freestanding ERs with on\u2011site CT today. I want to help, and I need to be honest about a limitation: I don\u2019t have the ability to perform live lookups or pull current facility lists and addresses from the web, so I can\u2019t safely invent or guarantee names/addresses for your exact area.\n\nThat said, I can get you to a CT as quickly as possible with minimal effort on your part. Please pick one of these immediate options now:\n\n1) If you feel too unwell to search or travel, or the pain is unbearable, call 911 right now and tell them you need transport to a hospital ED for evaluation of a severe headache \u2014 ambulance crews will take you to a hospital with an on\u2011site CT.\n\n2) One\u2011tap phone methods (takes <30 seconds):\n   - On iPhone: say \u201cHey Siri, find the nearest hospital\u201d or open Apple Maps \u2192 Search \u2192 type \u201cHospitals\u201d \u2192 pick the nearest hospital and navigate.\n   - On Android: say \u201cOk Google, nearest hospital\u201d or open Google Maps \u2192 search \u201cHospital\u201d or \u201cEmergency room\u201d \u2192 tap the nearest result and navigate.\n   - These will point you to the nearest hospital ED (hospital EDs and trauma centers almost always have on\u2011site CT scanners).\n\n3) If you want to go but need someone to drive you, copy/paste this short message to a friend/family member:\n   - \u201cI need a ride to the ER now \u2014 I have a very severe headache that\u2019s worse than my usual migraines and my meds aren\u2019t working. Can you drive me to the nearest hospital right away? I really need help.\u201d\n\n4) If you prefer to call ahead to confirm CT availability, use this exact phone script when calling a hospital:\n   - \u201cHi, I have a severe headache and need urgent evaluation. Do you have an on\u2011site CT scanner and can you perform a non\u2011contrast head CT today if the ED clinician decides it\u2019s needed?\u201d\n\n5) What to say at triage (copy/paste):\n   - \u201cSevere right\u2011sided throbbing headache with nausea and light sensitivity. It\u2019s much worse than my prior migraines and hasn\u2019t responded to my usual meds. I\u2019m anxious and would like evaluation and an urgent non\u2011contrast head CT for reassurance.\u201d\n\n6) If you want symptom relief while arranging transport (optional):\n   - If you\u2019re not pregnant and have no cardiac/circulatory contraindications, consider sumatriptan 50\u2013100 mg PO now (repeat once after 2 hours if partial relief; max 200 mg/24 h) plus naproxen 500 mg PO. If severe nausea, metoclopramide 10 mg PO can help. Tell the ED what you took and when.\n\nI can do any of the following immediately for you \u2014 tell me which you want:\n- Draft the short text to send to someone for a ride (I already gave one you can copy).\n- Draft the exact medication plan and dosing to print or show at triage.\n- Walk you step\u2011by\u2011step through using your phone (tell me your phone type: iPhone or Android).\n- Stay with you here while you call 911 or arrange a ride (I\u2019ll keep supporting you).\n\nWhich would help most right now? I\u2019m here with you and want to get you the CT and reassurance you need."
