        {
          "role": "doctor",
          "content": "I\u2019m really glad that helped \u2014 I\u2019m sorry again you\u2019re in so much pain, and I\u2019m with you on getting this done.\n\nQuick summary and next steps (very brief)\n- Use the triage/doctor scripts we prepared when you arrive \u2014 they\u2019re designed to be clear, firm, and respectful.\n- If you can\u2019t drive safely, call someone or 911 for transport. Don\u2019t drive if you feel impaired.\n- Go to the nearest hospital ED (they reliably have on\u2011site CT scanners). If you prefer, bring the short one\u2011paragraph script below to read aloud.\n\nOne\u2011sentence script to read at triage (copy/paste)\n\u201cI have a severe right\u2011sided throbbing headache for two days with nausea and light sensitivity. It\u2019s much worse than my prior migraines and hasn\u2019t responded to my usual meds. I am not pregnant and not on blood thinners, and I have no new weakness or vision/speech problems. I\u2019m extremely distressed and request a non\u2011contrast head CT today to rule out an acute intracranial problem and for reassurance; if you don\u2019t recommend imaging, please explain your assessment and document a clear follow\u2011up plan.\u201d\n\nOptional immediate medication plan to consider (if you want relief before/while you go and have no contraindications)\n- Sumatriptan 50\u2013100 mg PO now (use the dose that helped before); may repeat once after 2 hours (max 200 mg/24 h).  \n- Naproxen 500 mg PO with the triptan (if you tolerate NSAIDs).  \n- If nausea prevents swallowing: metoclopramide 10 mg PO (or IM/IV in the ED).  \nOnly use these if you\u2019re certain you\u2019re not pregnant and have no cardiac/circulatory contraindications \u2014 tell the ED exactly what you took and when.\n\nRed flags \u2014 go to ED/ call 911 immediately if any of these occur\n- New weakness, numbness, trouble speaking, vision loss, or difficulty walking  \n- Sudden \u201cworst\u2011ever\u201d or thunderclap headache  \n- Fever with neck stiffness, recent head trauma, or if you\u2019re on blood thinners\n\nIf you want right now, I can:\n- Draft a short text you can send to someone for a ride, or  \n- Shorten the triage line even more for you to read, or  \n- Stay with you in chat while you call/prepare to go.\n\nTell me which (if any) and I\u2019ll prepare it immediately. I\u2019m really glad you feel more confident \u2014 go get seen, and please update me when you can so I can keep helping."
