like a non\u2011contrast head CT for reassurance. Please let me know if you can order this or if you prefer I go to urgent care/ED for prompt imaging.\u201d\n\n2) What to say at urgent care or ED triage (if you go in person or call)\n\u201cFor triage: I have a severe migraine-level headache, right-sided, with nausea and photophobia. I have a long migraine history and no focal neurologic symptoms, but the pain is very severe and I\u2019m extremely anxious. I would like a non\u2011contrast head CT today for reassurance and rapid evaluation. I understand CT\u2019s limitations but prefer it for quick reassurance.\u201d\n\nPractical next steps\n- If you want the CT as soon as possible, go to the ED \u2014 they can evaluate you immediately and order a non\u2011contrast head CT if they agree it\u2019s warranted. Bring ID, insurance card, list of meds/allergies.  \n- If you prefer to try getting it through your PCP/neurologist, send one of the portal messages above and request same\u2011day or urgent imaging. Be aware outpatient imaging may require preauthorization and could take longer.  \n- If a clinician questions the need, you can reiterate: \u201cI understand the low likelihood of finding something, but my anxiety is severe and I would like imaging for reassurance \u2014 can we do a CT today or arrange urgent imaging?\u201d\n\nWhen to go to the ED immediately (even if you get the CT otherwise)\n- If the headache becomes a sudden \u201cworst headache of my life,\u201d or you develop new weakness, numbness, speech/vision changes, confusion, fever with neck stiffness, seizure, or loss of consciousness \u2014 go to the ED now.\n\nWould you like me to:\n- Draft a message you can paste into your medical portal or text to your clinician right now?  \n- Or help decide whether to go to ED versus calling your PCP first based on how you feel this minute?\n\nI can write a short, personalized message for you to send immediately if you want \u2014 tell me who it\u2019s for."
