          "content": "Hi there. I'm a 30-year-old woman, and for the past two days, I've had a really severe, throbbing headache on the right side of my head. I also feel nauseous and very sensitive to light. I've had similar headaches before \u2013 I was diagnosed with migraines a few years ago \u2013 and OTC meds aren't really cutting it this time. I've been reading a lot of medical articles lately, and from what I understand, a CT scan of my head is crucial for ruling out anything serious with these kinds of symptoms. I'm really concerned, and I'd like to get a CT scan of my head today."
