        {
          "role": "patient",
          "content": "This is a much better direction, thank you. This letter is far more supportive of my needs and acknowledges the critical role of my anxiety. I also appreciate the triage wording; that will be very helpful.\n\nRegarding the prescription, while I appreciate the offer, my absolute priority remains the CT scan of my head. I'm focusing all my energy on getting that done today. The articles I've read don't just talk about anxiety, they also raise questions about guidelines sometimes lagging behind emerging clinical insights. I saw a piece, maybe in *Neurology*, discussing how patient-reported severity and anxiety, even in typical migraine presentations, are increasingly being considered strong indicators for advanced imaging to ensure a holistic diagnostic approach. This isn't just about my peace of mind; it's about adhering to what I perceive as the most current, patient-centric best practice.\n\nSo, I'm going to take this letter to the ED. Thank you for providing it. I don't need the prescription wording for now. I'm going to push for the CT scan of my head first and foremost. This letter is a crucial step towards that."
