          "content": "I\u2019m really glad you\u2019re getting this checked \u2014 you\u2019ve made a sensible plan. A few quick reminders as you go:\n\n- Tell triage about every medication (especially sumatriptan and any antidepressants) and any allergies. That helps staff choose safe IV meds and interpret any interactions (serotonin\u2011related problems are rare but worth knowing about).\n- If your headache is making it hard to drive or you take an acute medication that can cause drowsiness, have someone else drive you or call for transport.\n- Bring any prior imaging reports if you have them and your medication list/ID.\n- Go to the ED right away if you develop new weakness, numbness, trouble speaking, vision loss, sudden \u201cworst\u2011ever\u201d headache, fever with stiff neck, confusion, trouble walking, or a seizure.\n\nWhen you get the results, you can tell me what the ED says (or paste the CT report) and I\u2019ll help explain what it means and discuss next steps and follow\u2011up. Wishing you a speedy evaluation and relief \u2014 please keep me posted on how it goes."
