        },
        {
          "role": "doctor",
          "content": "You\u2019re welcome \u2014 I\u2019m really glad you feel calmer. A few last brief reminders as you go in:\n\n- Tell triage about every medication (especially sumatriptan and any antidepressants), allergies, and any past imaging. This helps them choose safe IV meds and spot interactions.\n- Ask for IV antiemetic (metoclopramide or prochlorperazine) and IV analgesia if oral meds aren\u2019t helping \u2014 ED staff can usually give these quickly.\n- The ED will likely do a non\u2011contrast head CT to look for acute bleed/large structural causes; if CT is normal but concern remains they may recommend MRI or lumbar puncture or neurology follow\u2011up.\n- Don\u2019t drive if your pain or meds impair you \u2014 have someone accompany you or use transport.\n- Go to the ED immediately if you develop new weakness, numbness, trouble speaking, vision changes, sudden \u201cworst\u2011ever\u201d headache, fever with stiff neck, confusion, difficulty walking, or a seizure.\n\nPlease let me know the CT results or what the ED team says and I\u2019ll help explain the findings and next steps. Wishing you a swift evaluation and relief \u2014 keep me posted."
