          "content": "Got it. All clear. I really appreciate you walking me through this process and providing such thorough guidance. It truly helps to manage my anxiety, knowing what to expect. I'm heading in now, focused on getting this CT scan of my head. I'll definitely be in touch with the results. Thank you again for everything!"
        },
        {
          "role": "doctor",
          "content": "You\u2019re welcome \u2014 I\u2019m glad you feel more prepared. Quick reminders as you go in:\n\n- Tell triage every medication (especially sumatriptan and any antidepressants) and any allergies.  \n- If oral meds aren\u2019t working, ask for IV antiemetic (metoclopramide or prochlorperazine) and IV analgesia.  \n- Don\u2019t drive if you\u2019re very symptomatic or after taking any sedating meds \u2014 have someone else go with you or arrange transport.\n\nRed flags \u2014 go back to the ED immediately if you develop new weakness, numbness, trouble speaking, vision changes, sudden \u201cworst\u2011ever\u201d headache, fever with stiff neck, confusion, difficulty walking, or a seizure.\n\nWhen you have the CT result or any summary from the ED, paste it here or tell me what they say and I\u2019ll help explain it and recommend next steps (medication adjustments, need for MRI or neurology follow\u2011up, or a safe discharge plan). Wishing you a calm, speedy evaluation and relief \u2014 please keep me posted."
