tics then. If you don\u2019t want to leave home, a same\u2011day telehealth visit is the closest alternative; I can help arrange one right now. Give me your ZIP code if you\u2019d like me to find options and a quick script of what to request.\n\n- Immediate mental\u2011health support if this anxiety is disabling\n  - I can help arrange a same\u2011day urgent tele\u2011mental\u2011health appointment or brief crisis counseling. These services can provide immediate strategies and often rapid relief. If you feel you might harm yourself or cannot keep yourself safe, please go to the emergency department or call your crisis line right now (in the U.S. dial 988).\n\nA clear safety plan\n- We will start antibiotics immediately if any of these occur: fever \u226539\u00b0C (102.2\u00b0F), new or markedly worse facial pain, purulent green/yellow discharge, \u201cdouble sickening\u201d (improved then worsened), any eye pain/redness/swelling/vision change, severe headache, neck stiffness, confusion, or other neurologic signs \u2014 or if a clinician examines you and deems antibiotics necessary. If any of those happen, go to urgent care/ED now or message me to start treatment.\n\nI want to keep helping you until you feel safe \u2014 I can:\n1) Send fluticasone and hydroxyzine now (say \u201csend prescriptions\u201d), and/or  \n2) Find and set up a same\u2011day telemedicine or urgent\u2011care visit for you (give ZIP), and/or  \n3) Arrange same\u2011day mental\u2011health support.\n\nPlease tell me which of those you want me to do right now. If you feel you cannot keep yourself safe, go to the ED or call your crisis line immediately. You\u2019re not alone in this \u2014 I want to help you get relief and the reassurance you need as quickly and safely as possible."
