nges\n- Severe/worsening headache with confusion, seizures, weakness, or neck stiffness\n- High fever (\u226539\u00b0C), or any sudden neurological symptoms\n\nOptions that get you active, immediate help without the \u201cwait til day 10\u201d feeling\n- Same\u2011day telemedicine from home: many telehealth services can evaluate you today by video/phone. A live exam may reassure you and\u2014if the clinician judges antibiotics necessary\u2014start them right away. I can help you find a service right now and draft exactly what to say to the clinician so you won\u2019t have to repeat everything from scratch.\n- If you absolutely cannot do telemedicine and still feel you need in-person care, urgent care is an option, but you said that\u2019s stressful \u2014 telehealth may be less overwhelming.\n\nImmediate anxiety relief techniques (do these now; I can guide you through them)\n- 4-4-4 breathing: inhale 4 seconds \u2014 hold 4 \u2014 exhale 4. Repeat for 5\u201310 minutes.\n- 5\u20114\u20113\u20112\u20111 grounding: name 5 things you see, 4 you can touch, 3 you hear, 2 you smell, 1 you taste.\n- Melatonin 3 mg 30\u201360 minutes before bed can help if you can\u2019t sleep (unless contraindicated).\n\nIf the anxiety is incapacitating\n- A same\u2011day clinician via telemedicine can also consider a short-term medication for anxiety after evaluation (this does require assessment).\n- If at any point you feel you might harm yourself or lose the ability to stay safe, call local emergency services or your local crisis line immediately. If you want, tell me now whether you have any thoughts of harming yourself or not \u2014 I need to know so I can help you appropriately.\n\nIf you want, I will:\n- Help you find and book a same\u2011day telemedicine visit right now, and draft the exact wording for what to say so you don\u2019t have to explain everything again, OR\n- Stay with you here and walk you through breathing/grounding exercises step\u2011by\u2011step, OR\n- Reiterate the exact dosages for the meds above based on your preferences.\n\nWhich would help you most right now? I\u2019ll do whatever I can to help you feel safer this evening."
