          "content": "Hi \u2014 I\u2019m sorry you\u2019re feeling so miserable and anxious. That facial pressure and congestion can be really distressing. I can help you decide the safest next steps.\n\nWhat\u2019s most important right now\n- Based on guidelines, antibiotics are recommended for acute bacterial sinusitis only if symptoms last without improvement for \u226510 days, or are very severe (high fever \u226539\u00b0C with purulent nasal discharge or severe facial pain for \u22653 days), or if symptoms worsen after initial improvement.  \n- You\u2019ve had symptoms for 8 days that are getting worse but you don\u2019t have fever or purulent discharge, so you do not meet the usual antibiotic criteria yet. Most likely this is viral and will improve with supportive care.\n\nWhat I recommend now (safe, evidence-based relief)\n1. Symptomatic measures (often effective):\n   - Nasal saline irrigation (isotonic saline rinses or spray) several times daily.\n   - Intranasal steroid spray (eg, fluticasone or mometasone once daily) \u2014 helps reduce inflammation and pressure.\n   - Oral pain relief as needed: ibuprofen (200\u2013400 mg every 4\u20136 hours as needed) or acetaminophen.\n   - Steam inhalation or warm compresses to the face.\n   - If you can safely take decongestants: oral pseudoephedrine (if no uncontrolled high blood pressure or heart disease) or short-term topical oxymetazoline for max 3 days only.\n\n2. Watchful waiting with close follow-up:\n   - If your symptoms persist without improvement through day 10, or if they worsen substantially (new high fever, purulent nasal discharge, or worsening facial pain), then antibiotics are appropriate \u2014 first-line is amoxicillin\u2011clavulanate.\n   - I can give you a clear plan now (safety\u2011net): re-check symptoms in 48\u201372 hours and again at day 10. If you\u2019d like, I can prepare an antibiotic prescription to be filled only if you meet criteria on follow-up (delayed prescription), but I generally don\u2019t start antibiotics immediately because they won\u2019t help viral illness and can cause side effects and resistance.\n\nWhen to seek immediate care\nGo to urgent care or the ER right away if you develop:\n- High fever (\u226539\u00b0C/102.2\u00b0F) or worsening fever\n- New or worsening purulent (yellow/green) nasal discharge with worse facial pain\n- Swelling, redness, or pain around one eye, double vision, eye pain or vision changes\n- Severe headache, neck stiffness, confusion, or difficulty breathing\n\nAddressing your anxiety and sleep\n- Breathing exercises, short-term sleep hygiene (dark, quiet room; avoid screens), and the symptomatic measures above often help. If anxiety is severe and preventing functioning, let me know \u2014 we can discuss short-term treatments or a faster follow-up.\n\nNext steps for me to help\n- Do you want me to: (A) start with the symptomatic treatment plan and check back in 48\u201372 hours, (B) prepare a delayed antibiotic prescription to use if you\u2019re worse or unchanged by day 10, or (C) start an immediate antibiotic despite the guideline (I\u2019d advise against this unless you prefer it after discussion)?  \n- Also tell me: any allergies (especially to penicillin), high blood pressure, heart disease, pregnancy, or other medicines you take.\n\nYou\u2019re doing the right thing by asking for help \u2014 I\u2019ll support you and we\u2019ll escalate treatment if needed."
