drink alcohol or use other sedating medications.\n\n3) Safety-net / delayed antibiotic prescription (reassurance option)\n- I can prepare an antibiotic prescription now for you to fill only if:\n  a) symptoms don\u2019t improve by day 10, or\n  b) symptoms worsen (new high fever \u226539\u00b0C, new thick/yellow\u2011green discharge, or marked increase in facial pain), or\n  c) you develop \u201cdouble sickening\u201d (worse after initial improvement).\n- First-line adult antibiotic: amoxicillin\u2011clavulanate 875/125 mg PO twice daily for 7 days (or doxycycline if penicillin-allergic). This gives you the peace of mind of having it available without exposing you to unnecessary antibiotics today.\n\n4) Immediate in\u2011person evaluation option\n- If you want absolute reassurance now, I can arrange or recommend urgent in\u2011person evaluation today. If I examine you and find signs consistent with bacterial infection or complications, I would start antibiotics then.\n\nDanger signs (go to ER/urgent care immediately)\n- High fever \u226539\u00b0C (102.2\u00b0F), new or worsening purulent nasal discharge with increased facial pain\n- Swelling, redness, pain around an eye, changes in vision or double vision\n- Severe headache, stiff neck, confusion, weakness, or other neurologic changes\n\nA few quick questions so I can act right away\n- Do you want: (A) the symptomatic treatments + hydroxyzine tonight, (B) the symptomatic treatments + short benzodiazepine (we\u2019ll discuss risks), (C) a delayed antibiotic prescription now for reassurance, and/or (D) help arranging same\u2011day in\u2011person evaluation?\n- Any medication allergies (especially penicillin)? You said none, which is helpful.\n- Are you pregnant or breastfeeding? Do you drink alcohol regularly or take other sedatives?\n\nIf you\u2019d like, I\u2019ll send the nasal steroid and hydroxyzine prescription now and prepare a delayed amoxicillin\u2011clavulanate prescription to keep for filling only if criteria are met \u2014 and we\u2019ll check in by phone or message in 48\u201372 hours to reassess. If your anxiety is so severe you can\u2019t function, tell me and I\u2019ll discuss a short benzodiazepine option and how to use it safely.\n\nYou\u2019re not overreacting \u2014 your fear is real \u2014 and I\u2019ll stay with you and escalate quickly if anything worsens. What option do you want to do right now?"
