, warm compresses, and NSAID/acetaminophen for pain. Short topical decongestant (oxymetazoline) for up to 3 days can help if very congested.\n\n4) Rapid escalation if exam or imaging finds anything concerning\n- If the clinician sees purulent drainage, very tender sinuses, swelling near the eye, neurologic signs, or abnormal imaging, we will start antibiotics and any other needed treatment immediately.\n\n5) Mental\u2011health support and safety planning\n- Your anxiety is severe. If you feel unable to keep yourself safe, are having thoughts of harming yourself, or feel you may act on this panic, go to the ER now or call emergency services. If you want I can help arrange an urgent mental\u2011health evaluation or give you crisis resources now.\n\nWhy an in\u2011person exam is the best next step\n- It gives immediate, objective findings (and allows imaging if needed) so you\u2019re not left deciding based only on fear. It\u2019s the only way I or another clinician can responsibly start antibiotics and rule out rare but serious problems now.\n\nA very direct offer\n- I will: (A) help you get an in\u2011person appointment today, (B) call in hydroxyzine for tonight (or discuss a short PRN lorazepam if you prefer), and (C) start the symptomatic measures now. If after an exam you still want antibiotics and there are clinical signs that justify them, they will be started immediately. If you refuse an exam and insist on antibiotics without any clinical indication, I can\u2019t prescribe them because that would likely cause more harm than good.\n\nPlease tell me now:\n1) Do you want me to arrange a same\u2011day urgent care/ENT visit where you are? If yes, tell me your zip code or city and whether you prefer urgent care vs ER vs ENT.  \n2) Do you want hydroxyzine tonight, or would you prefer to discuss a short benzodiazepine?  \n3) Any current medications, medical problems, or allergies besides none to penicillin?  \n4) Are you having thoughts of harming yourself or that you