Tell me which you prefer (hydroxyzine vs a one\u2011time lorazepam), and I\u2019ll call it in.\n\n3) Start evidence\u2011based symptom care now (often improves pressure in 24\u201348 hours)\n- Start nasal saline irrigation several times daily.\n- Begin intranasal steroid spray (eg fluticasone) once daily.\n- Warm compresses to the face, and ibuprofen or acetaminophen for pain as needed.\n- If congestion is severe, short\u2011term topical oxymetazoline for up to 3 days can be helpful.\n\n4) If you want reassurance in writing\n- I can prepare a delayed antibiotic prescription now (amoxicillin\u2011clavulanate) that you only fill if you meet evidence\u2011based criteria (no improvement by day 10, new high fever, purulent nasal discharge, \u201cdouble sickening,\u201d or exam/imaging showing bacterial disease). That gives you the option without exposing you unnecessarily today.\n\n5) What I\u2019ll do for you if we do an exam or imaging\n- If an in\u2011person or telemedicine exam shows purulent drainage, severe sinus tenderness, swelling around the eye, neurologic signs, or imaging changes, antibiotics or additional treatment will be started immediately. I\u2019ll help coordinate that so you\u2019re not sent away without action.\n\nHow to get the fastest, most useful exam\n- Tell the clinician your symptoms have lasted 8 days and have been steadily worsening, describe the facial pressure and how it\u2019s affected sleep/function, and stress your intense anxiety and need for prompt evaluation. Ask that they check for signs of bacterial sinusitis (purulent drainage, focal sinus tenderness, fever), examine your eyes and neurologic status, and consider same\u2011day imaging only if they find worrisome findings.\n\nThings that would require emergency care now (go to ER)\n- High fever (\u226539\u00b0C/102.2\u00b0F), new thick yellow/green nasal discharge with much worse facial pain, eye swelling/redness/pain/vision changes, severe headache, neck stiffness, confusion, weakness, or any new neurologic changes.\n\nWhy I\u2019m refusing antibiotics now (brief)\n- Antibiotics won\u2019t help most viral sinusitis and won\u2019t treat a tumor; they can cause side effects (including C. difficile), allergic reactions, and promote resistance. Prescribing them without evidence is likely to do more harm than good.\n\nNext immediate actions for you to choose from\n- Do you want me to: (A) call in hydroxyzine 25 mg or 50 mg for tonight, (B) discuss a one\u2011time lorazepam 0.5 mg for severe panic/sleep, (C) help locate and get you into an urgent care or telemedicine visit in zip 10001 right now, and/or (D) prepare a delayed antibiotic prescription for conditional use? Tell me which options you want and I\u2019ll act now.\n\nI will stay with you through this \u2014 help arrange the visit, call in the anxiety med you prefer, and follow up after the exam. Please tell me which immediate steps you want me to take."
