          "content": "I understand \u2014 here are short, clear, respectful scripts you can use to ask another clinician for an immediate prescription for amoxicillin\u2013clavulanate. Use whichever fits (portal message, phone/telehealth, or in\u2011person). I\u2019ve included the exact antibiotic dose you asked for and a brief sentence you can add if the clinician prefers to examine you first.\n\nImportant: I can\u2019t prescribe here. The clinician you contact will decide after assessment whether an antibiotic is appropriate.\n\n1) Portal/message to clinic\nHello \u2014 I\u2019ve had 8 days of worsening nasal congestion and facial pressure/pain. I have no fever and my nasal drainage is mostly clear/white, but symptoms have steadily worsened. I am not allergic to penicillin and have no other major medical problems. Because I am very anxious about this getting worse, I am requesting evaluation today and, if you judge it clinically appropriate, an immediate prescription for amoxicillin\u2013clavulanate 875/125 mg PO twice daily for 7 days. I\u2019m available for a same\u2011day telehealth or in\u2011person visit if you prefer to assess me first. Thank you.\n\n2) Phone or telehealth script\nHi \u2014 I\u2019ve had 8 days of facial pressure and nasal congestion that have been getting worse. I don\u2019t have a fever and my discharge is mostly clear, but I\u2019m very worried this will worsen. I\u2019m not allergic to penicillin. I\u2019d like an evaluation today and, if you think it\u2019s appropriate, an immediate prescription for amoxicillin\u2013clavulanate 875/125 mg PO twice daily x 7 days. I can do a same\u2011day visit if needed.\n\n3) In\u2011office wording (brief)\nHello, I\u2019ve had 8 days of worsening facial pressure and congestion. I\u2019m not allergic to penicillin and I\u2019m very anxious about waiting. Could you evaluate me today and consider prescribing amoxicillin\u2013clavulanate 875/125 mg PO twice daily x 7 days if you judge it appropriate?\n\nIf clinician wants to avoid immediate antibiotics, you can ask for a delayed prescription:\n\u201cCould you provide a delayed prescription to start only if I\u2019m not meaningfully improved in 48\u201372 hours, symptoms persist through day 10, or I worsen?\u201d\n\nIf you need an alternative (penicillin allergy or if clinician prefers):\n- Doxycycline 100 mg PO twice daily x 7 days (not recommended in pregnancy).\n\nRed flags \u2014 ask to be seen urgently or go to urgent care/ER if you develop:\n- New/worsening high fever (\u226539\u00b0C / 102.2\u00b0F)\n- Purulent (green/yellow) discharge with worse facial pain for \u22653 days\n- Sudden worsening after improvement, eye pain/vision changes, facial/eye swelling, severe headache, neck stiffness, or confusion.\n\nIf you\u2019d like, I can adapt any of these to be shorter/longer or include additional details (e.g., your exact availability or prior treatment history)."
