ng and calming anxiety for a few nights. Tell me if you have glaucoma, enlarged prostate, or are pregnant/breastfeeding.  \n   - Non-drug strategies now: 4-4-8 breathing, warm compresses to face, steam before bed, limit caffeine, and sleep hygiene. I can also suggest a single low-dose sleep aid like trazodone if you prefer \u2014 tell me if you\u2019ve tried these before.\n\n4) Safety-net / conditional antibiotic plan (keeps you safe without unnecessary antibiotics)\n   - If you prefer, I\u2019ll provide a delayed antibiotic prescription with explicit instructions to fill only if any of the following occur: symptoms persist without improvement through day 10, new fever \u226539.0\u00b0C (102.2\u00b0F) with purulent discharge or severe facial pain for \u22653 days, \u201cdouble sickening,\u201d or any eye pain/swelling or vision changes. Or we can agree that if your in-person/video exam suggests bacterial infection, we\u2019ll start antibiotics immediately.  \n   - If you adamantly refuse a delayed plan and still want an immediate antibiotic despite counseling, I need to be honest: I cannot recommend that because it\u2019s unlikely to help and may harm you. However, I will do everything possible now to get you an immediate exam and to treat your anxiety so you can function.\n\nWhen to go to the ER now\n- Any new eye pain/redness/swelling or vision changes, severe/worsening headache or neck stiffness, confusion, or marked facial swelling \u2014 go to the ED immediately.\n\nNext step \u2014 what would help you most right now?\nPlease tell me:\n- Do you want me to arrange a same-day in-person visit or a video visit now? (I recommend this if your fear makes you unable to wait.)  \n- Do you want prescriptions now for fluticasone, saline instructions, analgesic, and short-term hydroxyzine 25 mg at bedtime to help you sleep?  \n- Are you pregnant, breastfeeding, or do you have glaucoma or prostate issues? Any medication allergies?  \n\nI want to keep you safe and get you relief as quickly as possible \u2014 tell me which option feels best and I\u2019ll act immediately."
