begin treatment if there are any concerning findings.\n\n3) If you prefer to avoid ED/urgent care right now, I will:\n   - Provide the prescriptions above and a plan for close follow-up (check-in within 24\u201348 hours).  \n   - Provide a clear \u201csafety-net\u201d plan: fill antibiotics only if symptoms meet criteria (no improvement by day 10, new high fever \u226539\u00b0C with purulent discharge or severe facial pain for \u22653 days, or \u201cdouble sickening\u201d), or if an in-person exam indicates bacterial infection. I realize delayed Rx doesn\u2019t ease your fear \u2014 that\u2019s why I recommend the immediate exam if you feel you cannot tolerate the possibility even briefly.\n\n4) When to go to the emergency department now\n   - New/worsening eye pain, redness, swelling, or vision changes  \n   - New fever \u226539.0\u00b0C (102.2\u00b0F) with purulent nasal discharge or severe facial pain for \u22653 days  \n   - Severe/worsening headache, neck stiffness, confusion, focal neurologic signs, or marked facial swelling\n\nIf you want, I can immediately prescribe the intranasal steroid and hydroxyzine tonight and give clear written instructions for saline irrigation and analgesics. I can also help you plan the quickest route to urgent care or the ED (what to say, what to ask them to check). If you would like me to proceed with those prescriptions now, tell me and I\u2019ll write them and give dosing/duration and precautions.\n\nI genuinely want to keep you safe and to reduce your suffering. If you decide you still need antibiotics despite this counseling, please go to urgent care or the ED right away so a clinician can examine you and prescribe them only if truly indicated."
