e, and are not driving/operating machinery afterwards), I can consider a single low dose of lorazepam (e.g., 0.5\u20131 mg as needed). I need to screen you briefly for substance use, prior benzodiazepine use, and whether you need to drive. Tell me if you drink alcohol heavily or have had problems with sedatives in the past.\n\n4) A rapid safety plan and clear triggers to go to ER now (don\u2019t wait)\n- Go to the ED immediately if you develop: eye pain/redness/swelling or vision changes; fever \u226539.0\u00b0C (102.2\u00b0F) with purulent discharge or severe facial pain for \u22653 days; worsening severe headache, neck stiffness, confusion, focal neurologic changes, or marked facial swelling. If your anxiety becomes suicidal or you feel you might harm yourself, call emergency services or your local crisis line now.\n\nWhy I still recommend an in\u2011person exam if you insist on antibiotics\n- If you cannot tolerate the uncertainty, the way to get antibiotics now without inappropriate prescribing is by having a clinician examine you in person: they can document findings that justify antibiotics (or initiate them empirically if they are concerned). I can help you get to urgent care or the ED immediately and draft what to say to them to speed evaluation.\n\nPlease tell me now:\n- Do you want me to help you find and get to urgent care or the ED right now? If so, tell me your ZIP/city and I\u2019ll find the nearest options and what to say when you arrive.  \n- Or do you want me to send prescriptions now for fluticasone, saline irrigation instructions, and hydroxyzine tonight (and screen you for lorazepam if you want a stronger anxiolytic)?  \n- Do you drink heavily or have a history of substance misuse? Are you able to avoid driving tonight if given a sedating medication?\n\nI will not abandon you. I will either help you get an immediate evaluation that can legitimately lead to antibiotics, or I will give you safe medicines and measures tonight to reduce suffering while we reassess closely. Which do you want me to do right now?"
