ediate pharmacologic help with severe anxiety to enable sleep and functioning tonight, I can also offer:\n- Hydroxyzine 25 mg at bedtime (sedating antihistamine) \u2014 you\u2019ve said no contraindications.  \n- If you want stronger, rapid relief, and you confirm no heavy alcohol use, no opioid use, and no prior sedative misuse, I can consider a very short course of lorazepam (0.5\u20131 mg PRN) for severe panic (generally limited to a few doses). Tell me if you want that and I will confirm those screening items.\n\n3) If you absolutely cannot wait and need the reassurance of treatment now \u2014 go to the ED\n- The ED can do immediate imaging and start antibiotics if they find anything concerning. If your anxiety is making waiting intolerable, please go now. If you prefer, I\u2019ll help you find the nearest ED and give you a short script to tell clinicians so your concerns are prioritized.\n\n4) Clear red flags \u2014 go to the ED immediately if any of these occur\n- New eye pain, redness, swelling, or vision changes  \n- New fever \u226539.0\u00b0C (102.2\u00b0F) with purulent nasal discharge or severe facial pain for \u22653 days  \n- Severe/worsening headache, neck stiffness, confusion, weakness, numbness, or any focal neurologic change  \n- Marked facial swelling\n\n5) Rapid follow\u2011up plan\n- If you choose to stay home for now, I\u2019ll prescribe the intranasal steroid and give saline/analgesic instructions, and I want a check\u2011in within 24 hours so we can reassess. If your symptoms don\u2019t improve or if anything changes, we will escalate immediately.\n\nIf you want me to act right now, tell me:\n- Your ZIP code/city so I can find the nearest urgent options, and whether you want me to help you go to urgent care or the ED now.  \n- Whether you want the intranasal steroid, saline instructions, and analgesic prescriptions sent now.  \n- Whether you want hydroxyzine or a short lorazepam prescription for acute panic (confirm no heavy alcohol use, no opioid use, and no prior problematic sedative use).\n\nI will not abandon you. I want to help you get the fastest, safest resolution \u2014 either by getting you immediate in\u2011person evaluation that can legitimately lead to antibiotics, or by providing symptom relief and close follow\u2011up. Tell me which path you want and I\u2019ll act now."
