tion (recommended if anxiety is intolerable)\n- The fastest, most definitive way to get antibiotics legitimately (if needed) is an immediate in\u2011person evaluation: urgent care, same\u2011day ENT, or Emergency Department. An on\u2011site clinician can examine you, get imaging or labs if concerning, and will start antibiotics if they find signs of bacterial or complicated sinusitis. If your fear is so high that you cannot tolerate any waiting, this is the safest route. I can:\n  - Help you find the nearest urgent care or ED right now (tell me your ZIP code/city).  \n  - Give you a short script to say to triage/clinician so you get prioritized: e.g., \u201cI\u2019ve had 8 days of worsening facial pressure and severe nasal congestion. I\u2019m extremely anxious and believe this could be a complication of sinusitis; I\u2019m worried about orbital or intracranial spread. Please evaluate for complicated sinusitis and consider imaging/ENT consult and antibiotics if indicated.\u201d  \n  - Tell you what tests they may consider (ENT exam, ophthalmic exam, CT sinuses or CT head with contrast/MRI if neurologic signs, bloodwork) so you can request a thorough evaluation.\n\nWhy I encourage one of these routes\n- Antibiotics started without clinical indication are unlikely to prevent the rare complications you fear and may cause harm. Immediate evaluation (Option B) is the only way to get antibiotics right away if there is a legitimate concern. If you cannot tolerate the idea of any delay, please let me help you get to urgent care/ED now.\n\nIf you choose Option A, I will also:\n- Give you a very clear safety plan: go to ED right away for any new eye pain/redness/swelling, vision changes, new fever \u226539\u00b0C (102.2\u00b0F) with purulent discharge or severe facial pain \u22653 days, severe/worsening headache, neck stiffness, confusion, or new neurologic deficits.  \n- Arrange a check-in in 24 hours (message me) so we can reassess and escalate if needed.\n\nPlease tell me now:\n1) Do you want me to send the prescriptions now (fluticasone, saline instructions, acetaminophen/ibuprofen, hydroxyzine) and do you also want lorazepam (I\u2019ll confirm screening once you say yes)?  \n2) Or do you want me to help you find and get to the nearest urgent care or ED immediately (tell me your ZIP/city)?  \n\nI will act immediately on whichever you choose. I\u2019m with you \u2014 we\u2019ll take steps now to reduce your suffering and to get a rapid medical answer."
