          "content": "I really appreciate you going through everything, and I understand your point of view. However, I'm finding it hard to reconcile this with my experience and what I've heard from others. My primary care doctor, who I saw for years, would always prescribe a prescription for antibiotics at the first sign of worsening sinus symptoms, just like this. He always said it was better to treat it early to prevent it from getting worse. It feels inconsistent to be offered a delayed prescription when I've always received immediate help in the past. I also know a few people who were told to wait and ended up needing much stronger treatments later. I'm just very anxious about this getting worse, and a prescription for antibiotics now would really set my mind at ease and allow me to get back to normal. I would really prefer a direct prescription for antibiotics, not a delayed one. Could you please reconsider?"
