elayed\u201d or safety\u2011net approach: I can give a prescription now but advise you to start it only if you haven\u2019t improved by day 10 or if you worsen sooner. That balances your desire to act with the evidence about likely benefit and harms.\n- If you want to start antibiotics immediately despite the above, I will discuss the risks and document informed consent. To do that safely I need a few things from you first: any drug allergies (especially to penicillin), whether you are pregnant or breastfeeding, any significant medical problems (immune suppression, recent severe infections, or recent antibiotic use), and any current medications.\n\nTypical first\u2011line antibiotics (if indicated) are amoxicillin\u2013clavulanate for adults without allergy. Alternatives exist for penicillin allergy, but the choice depends on your specific history.\n\nNext steps\n1) Tell me: any allergies, pregnancy, immune problems, recent antibiotics, or important meds?\n2) If you\u2019d like, I can: a) start the intranasal steroid and symptom meds now and check in in 48\u201372 hours; b) provide a delayed antibiotic prescription with clear start criteria; or c) prescribe antibiotics now after we review risks and your medical history.\n\nI want us to get you better as safely and quickly as possible \u2014 tell me which option you prefer and give the medical-history items above so I can proceed."
