urs after starting, contact me so we can reassess \u2014 we may need an in\u2011person exam, imaging, or a different therapy.\n- Continue supportive measures now: nasal saline irrigation, intranasal steroid spray (fluticasone or mometasone) daily, acetaminophen or ibuprofen for pain, short-term topical decongestant (oxymetazoline) no more than 3 days or oral pseudoephedrine if you can take it.\n\nDocumentation of informed consent\n- You have stated you understand that current guidelines suggest antibiotics are unlikely to help at this stage, and you accept the possible risks (allergic reaction, GI side effects, C. difficile, and antibiotic resistance) and still wish to start amoxicillin\u2013clavulanate today. I have explained why I would typically wait or use a delayed prescription approach, and you understand the reasoning.\n\nNext step\n- Tell me your pharmacy name and city (or whether you prefer a printed/written prescription to pick up), and I will (virtually) finalize the prescription details so you can obtain it promptly. If you\u2019d rather get this done in person, I can arrange an expedited in\u2011office or urgent\u2011care visit for immediate prescribing and exam.\n\nI want you to get relief and I\u2019ll follow closely \u2014 please confirm your age \u226518 and that you have no liver disease (or tell me if you do) so I can proceed."
