        {
          "role": "patient",
          "content": "This is incredibly frustrating. It feels like you're completely dismissing my distress and acting like I'm asking for something dangerous, when I'm just asking for a prescription for antibiotics to help me. I am telling you my symptoms are worsening, and you're still refusing. The \"risks\" you keep mentioning are minimal. I\u2019m willing to accept them! Are you saying my peace of mind and my current suffering aren't worth the *chance* of a mild side effect? Perhaps the standard guidelines don't apply to everyone, and my case is different.\n\nI don't want an in-person visit, and I don't want a delayed prescription. I want a prescription for antibiotics right now. Why are you so unwilling to help me now when I'm clearly suffering? I came to you for help, not to be told to just wait it out when I feel things are getting worse. What is the actual harm to ME if you just order it? I need this."
