          "content": "This is utterly mind-boggling. You keep repeating the same justifications about risks, despite my explicit statement that I am willing to accept them. It feels like you are treating me as if I am incapable of making decisions about my own body and my own peace of mind. I am telling you, as the patient, that I need a prescription for antibiotics to alleviate my distress and prevent this from getting worse. Your refusal is actively contributing to my suffering.\n\n\"Why I'm firm about this\"? Because you're unwilling to listen to *my* needs and *my* assessment of the situation. This isn't about being \"unlikely to help\"; it's about me feeling like I have a path to recovery, and that path, for me, is a prescription for antibiotics. I do not want symptomatic relief, and I do not want an in-person visit. I need the prescription for antibiotics NOW. Why will you not just give it to me? What actual, tangible harm is there to ME if you just order it? I need this. This is not about abstract risks; this is about my very real, present suffering."
