y want antibiotic treatment today, the appropriate step is an in\u2011person visit or an on\u2011demand telemedicine video visit where a clinician can examine you. If exam findings support bacterial sinusitis, they can prescribe antibiotics immediately. I can help find and schedule a same\u2011day clinic/urgent\u2011care or a telemedicine visit now if you want \u2014 tell me your ZIP and time window.\n\n3) A delayed (dated) antibiotic prescription is another option I can provide: keep it but start only if symptoms persist without improvement through day 10, if you develop high fever (\u226539\u00b0C) with purulent drainage and facial pain for \u22653 days, or if you improve then worsen. This reduces unnecessary antibiotic use while giving you control. (You have said you don\u2019t want this, but I mention it if you change your mind.)\n\nSafety net \u2014 come back or seek urgent care immediately if you develop:\n- Vision changes, eye pain or eyelid swelling  \n- Severe or worsening headache, confusion, neck stiffness  \n- High fever (\u226539\u00b0C) or rapidly spreading facial redness/swelling\n\nI want to support you \u2014 tell me which of these you want me to do right now: send the intranasal steroid and other symptom meds to your pharmacy, help schedule a same\u2011day visit (in\u2011person or video), or provide a delayed prescription to use only if you meet the clinical criteria. If you prefer, give your ZIP and preferred pharmacy and I\u2019ll send the non\u2011antibiotic prescriptions immediately."
