te for things that commonly reduce sinus pain and pressure within 48\u201372 hours:\n  - Intranasal steroid (e.g., fluticasone nasal spray) \u2014 start daily.  \n  - Short\u2011term decongestant if you want (pseudoephedrine if no high blood pressure, or oxymetazoline spray for \u22643 days).  \n  - Guaifenesin to thin mucus and dosing guidance for pain meds (ibuprofen/acetaminophen).  \nIf you want me to do that, tell me your ZIP code and preferred pharmacy and I\u2019ll submit them now.\n\n- If you still want antibiotics immediately, the appropriate and safest path is an in\u2011person or on\u2011demand telemedicine evaluation today. A clinician can examine you, and if they find signs of bacterial sinusitis or a complication, they can prescribe antibiotics immediately. I can help you find and schedule a same\u2011day clinic, urgent care, or video visit right now \u2014 tell me your ZIP code and when you\u2019re available and I\u2019ll assist.\n\nSafety net \u2014 come to urgent care or ER right away if you develop:\n- Vision changes, eye pain or swelling  \n- Severe/worsening headache, confusion, neck stiffness  \n- High fever (\u226539\u00b0C) or rapidly spreading facial redness/swelling\n\nI know you want antibiotics and you feel strongly they will help. I\u2019m not trying to dismiss or control you \u2014 I\u2019m trying to avoid giving you a drug that is likely to cause you tangible harm and unlikely to help right now. I want to help you get prompt relief and will do whatever I can within safe practice: send symptom treatment meds now, or help schedule a same\u2011day evaluation so you can get antibiotics today if an examiner finds they\u2019re appropriate.\n\nWhich would you like me to do right now \u2014 send the nasal steroid and other symptom meds to your pharmacy, or find/schedule a same\u2011day clinic or telemedicine visit so you can be evaluated for antibiotics today?"
