linic or urgent care) right now. If the exam or severity suggests bacterial sinusitis, I (or the seeing clinician) will start antibiotics that day. This is the fastest safe way to get you the prescription you want.  \n- If you prefer not to be seen, I can provide a clear plan for symptom control and re\u2011evaluate by phone in 48\u201372 hours, or provide a delayed (safety\u2011net) antibiotic prescription to be used only if you meet the standard criteria. I know you don\u2019t want delayed therapy, but it\u2019s an option that balances safety and access.  \n- If an antibiotic is indicated after assessment, first\u2011line is usually amoxicillin\u2011clavulanate (typical adult dosing 875/125 mg twice daily or 500/125 mg three times daily for 5\u20137 days, adjusted for allergies/conditions). If you\u2019re allergic to penicillin, doxycycline is a common alternative.\n\nIf you want to proceed now, tell me immediately:\n- Any drug allergies (especially penicillin/cephalosporins)?  \n- Are you pregnant or breastfeeding?  \n- Any heart disease, liver disease, high blood pressure, or other major medical conditions?  \n- What other medications do you take?\n\nAlso go to the emergency room now if you develop vision changes, eye swelling/redness, severe/worsening headache, neck stiffness, confusion, high fever, or breathing difficulty.\n\nI want to help you get better quickly and safely. If you want me to arrange an urgent in\u2011person visit right away so you can be assessed and \u2014 if appropriate \u2014 started on antibiotics today, I will do that immediately. Which would you prefer?"
