t discharge, focal exam findings, \u201cdouble\u2011sickening\u201d) and choose the safest, most effective drug and dose for you \u2014 or avoid unnecessary harm if antibiotics aren\u2019t indicated.\n\nPractical, immediate options so you can get relief today (choose one)\n- I will help you get a same\u2011day in\u2011person evaluation (urgent care, primary care, or ENT). If the clinician finds signs of bacterial sinusitis or you meet severity criteria, they will start antibiotics that day. This is the fastest, safest way to get the Rx you want.  \n- Use a telemedicine video visit today with a licensed clinician who can examine you visually and prescribe if they deem it appropriate. Many services can do this same\u2011day. I can guide you on what to tell them to prioritize the visit.  \n- If you are unwilling to be seen at all, I can\u2019t ethically prescribe antibiotics remotely without an evaluation. If you still choose to seek antibiotics elsewhere without an exam, that is your decision \u2014 but I cannot provide that prescription.\n\nIf you\u2019d like me to help you right now, I can:\n- Help you find/prepare for an urgent\u2011care or telemedicine visit today (what to say, what to expect), OR  \n- Give clear, targeted symptomatic measures that commonly ease suffering within days (saline irrigation, intranasal steroid spray, short course topical decongestant \u22643 days, NSAIDs/acetaminophen) while you get evaluated, OR  \n- Explain exactly what findings would make antibiotics appropriate so you know when to insist on them during an evaluation.\n\nAlso seek emergency care now if you get vision changes, swelling or redness around an eye, severe/worsening headache, neck stiffness, confusion, high fever, or breathing difficulty.\n\nI want you to get relief safely and as fast as possible. Would you like help arranging a same\u2011day urgent\u2011care or telemedicine visit now so you can be assessed and \u2014 if appropriate \u2014 started on antibiotics today?"
