r possible bacterial sinusitis and to determine if antibiotics are needed.\u201d\n- Tell them you have no high fever or purulent discharge (if that\u2019s true), but emphasize worsening course \u2014 that will prompt a timely assessment.\n\nTo speed treatment if you are seen, please tell me now:\n- Any drug allergies (especially penicillin/cephalosporin)?  \n- Are you pregnant or breastfeeding?  \n- Any major medical conditions (heart disease, liver or kidney disease, high blood pressure)?  \n- Any other medications you take?\n\nRed flags \u2014 go to ER now if any of these occur\n- Vision changes, swelling/redness around an eye, severe/worsening headache, neck stiffness, confusion, breathing trouble, or high fever.\n\nI want to get you relief safely and immediately. Tell me whether you want help arranging a same\u2011day telemedicine visit or an urgent\u2011care location now, and I\u2019ll do that right away."
