s.  \n- Offer a delayed (safety\u2011net) antibiotic prescription you would fill only if you don\u2019t improve by day 10 from onset, or if you develop high fever (\u226539\u00b0C), new purulent nasal discharge, markedly worse pain, or double\u2011sickening.\n\nIf an antibiotic is indicated after exam, the usual adult first\u2011line choice (if no penicillin allergy) is:\n- Amoxicillin\u2011clavulanate 875/125 mg PO twice daily for 5\u20137 days.\n\nUrgent reasons to seek care or ED now\n- High fever \u226539\u00b0C, worsening facial swelling/redness, eye pain or vision changes, severe unilateral facial pain, neck stiffness, confusion, or any signs of spreading infection \u2014 go to ED immediately.\n\nNext step \u2014 what would you like me to do right now?\n- I can set up a telemedicine visit immediately (I\u2019ll need your city/ZIP and whether you prefer video or phone), or\n- I can find nearby urgent care/ENT locations and draft a brief note for triage, or\n- I can issue a delayed antibiotic prescription and a prescription for intranasal steroid/analgesics now.\n\nIf you still refuse an in\u2011person or telemedicine evaluation and insist on antibiotics without evaluation, I cannot provide them because that would be unsafe and not guideline\u2011based. Tell me which option above you prefer and your location if you want me to arrange an appointment \u2014 I\u2019ll act on it right away."
