elps reduce inflammation and can shorten symptoms.  \n   - Analgesic guidance: ibuprofen 200\u2013400 mg every 4\u20136 hrs as needed (unless contraindicated) or acetaminophen 500\u20131000 mg every 4\u20136 hrs as needed (observe max daily dose).  \n   - Short course topical nasal decongestant (oxymetazoline) only if severe congestion and for no more than 3 days to avoid rebound.\n\nIf antibiotics are prescribed after evaluation, the usual first\u2011line adult choice (if no penicillin allergy) is amoxicillin\u2011clavulanate 875/125 mg PO twice daily for 5\u20137 days.\n\nUrgent reasons to go to ED right now\n- High fever \u226539\u00b0C, worsening facial swelling/redness, eye pain or vision changes, severe unilateral facial pain, neck stiffness, confusion, or signs of spreading infection \u2014 go to ED immediately.\n\nNext step \u2014 tell me which you want:\nA) I\u2019ll find and help arrange a same\u2011day telemedicine or urgent care/ENT appointment near you (give city/ZIP and preference).  \nB) I\u2019ll provide a delayed antibiotic prescription and the intranasal steroid/analgesic prescriptions now.  \nC) I\u2019ll just send the intranasal steroid and analgesic prescriptions and help you monitor.\n\nI know this is frustrating. If you want me to find care right now, give your location and I\u2019ll act immediately."
