an help.\n- Steam/humidifier, hydration, rest.\n\nOptions to get antibiotics promptly if they are actually warranted\n- I can arrange an urgent in\u2011person or same\u2011day telemedicine visit (video preferred) today. An exam that shows purulent discharge, marked sinus tenderness, high fever, or other concerning signs would justify starting antibiotics now \u2014 and I will prescribe them immediately if I see that.\n- If you prefer not to do an in\u2011person visit, I can provide a delayed antibiotic prescription to start only if symptoms haven\u2019t improved by day 10 or if they worsen as described above. (I know you\u2019ve said you don\u2019t want delayed therapy; I\u2019m giving it as an option for those who want a safety net.)\n- If you insist on starting antibiotics without an exam or meeting criteria, I cannot in good conscience prescribe them because it would expose you to potential harm without demonstrated likely benefit.\n\nSafety warnings \u2014 come in urgently if any of these occur\n- New or worsening high fever (\u226539\u00b0C), severe or rapidly worsening facial pain\n- Eye pain, eye swelling, redness, or vision changes\n- Severe headache, neck stiffness, confusion, or any neurologic symptoms\n\nQuick questions to tailor care\n- What is your current temperature? Any new fever today?\n- Any one\u2011sided facial swelling, dental pain, eye symptoms, or severe headache?\n- Have you ever had recurrent sinus infections or sinus surgery?\n\nIf you want, I\u2019ll:\n- Start the intranasal steroid and supportive meds now (I can send prescriptions/over\u2011the\u2011counter recommendations), AND arrange an urgent in\u2011person or video visit today so we can reassess for antibiotics \u2014 would you like me to set that up?"
