stify antibiotics. If that exam shows bacterial sinusitis, we will prescribe antibiotics immediately. I can help arrange a same\u2011day urgent\u2011care or telemedicine visit today and notify that clinician of your symptoms so you don\u2019t have to \u201cconvince\u201d anyone \u2014 I\u2019ll advocate for timely evaluation.\n\nA compromise I can offer\n- If you want a safety net, I can also provide a delayed antibiotic prescription for you to start only if symptoms don\u2019t improve by day 10 or if they worsen before then. That preserves immediate control while avoiding unnecessary harm.\n\nWhen to get urgent care or emergency care now\n- New fever \u226539\u00b0C, severe or rapidly worsening facial pain, eye pain/swelling/vision changes, severe headache, neck stiffness, confusion, or other neurologic symptoms \u2014 go to urgent care/ED.\n\nI\u2019m not refusing to help \u2014 I\u2019m trying to help you in the way most likely to actually relieve your symptoms while protecting you from harms that do happen to real people. I can: (A) send the intranasal steroid and symptomatic meds now and detailed irrigation instructions, or (B) arrange a same\u2011day urgent or video visit so you can be examined and receive antibiotics today if clinically indicated, or (C) provide a delayed antibiotic prescription. Which would you like me to do right now?"
