ncerning findings). If that exam shows bacterial sinusitis, we will prescribe antibiotics at once. I can help arrange a same\u2011day urgent\u2011care or telemedicine visit and communicate your history to that team \u2014 would you like me to set that up now?\n- If you prefer not to be evaluated, I cannot ethically or safely prescribe antibiotics for you today given the low likelihood of benefit and the real personal risks.\n\nCompromise / safety net options\n- I can provide a delayed prescription to be used only if symptoms don\u2019t improve by day 10 or if you worsen before then \u2014 that preserves your control while avoiding unnecessary harm.\n- If you worsen now (see below), come to urgent care/ED immediately and we\u2019ll start antibiotics if indicated.\n\nUrgent warning signs (come in immediately)\n- New high fever (\u226539\u00b0C), sudden or rapidly worsening facial pain\n- Eye pain, swelling, redness, or vision changes\n- Severe headache, neck stiffness, confusion, or any new neurologic symptoms\n\nI want to help you get relief and will support whatever safe route you choose: send symptomatic prescriptions now, arrange a same\u2011day exam so antibiotics can be started if indicated, or provide a delayed prescription. Tell me which of those you want and I\u2019ll act right away."
