f symptoms persist without improvement to day 10, or become severe (fever \u226539\u00b0C, thick purulent discharge with worsening facial pain for \u22653 days), or you worsen after initial improvement, then antibiotics are appropriate \u2014 I can prescribe amoxicillin\u2013clavulanate (first\u2011line) at that time.\n\nIf you want antibiotics today despite my recommendation\n- The appropriate and safe way to start them immediately is to be examined (in\u2011person or same\u2011day video). If an exam shows purulent drainage, marked sinus tenderness, fever, or other signs of bacterial infection, I or another clinician can prescribe antibiotics at once. I can help arrange a same\u2011day urgent\u2011care or telemedicine visit and communicate your history so you don\u2019t have to \u201cconvince\u201d anyone \u2014 I\u2019ll advocate for a timely evaluation.\n\nUrgent warning signs \u2014 come in right away if you develop:\n- Fever \u226539\u00b0C, severe or rapidly worsening facial pain  \n- Eye pain, swelling, redness, or changes in vision  \n- Severe headache, neck stiffness, confusion, or neurologic symptoms\n\nI want to help you get relief. Tell me which of these you\u2019d like me to do now:\n1) Send prescriptions and step\u2011by\u2011step instructions for intranasal steroid and symptomatic care right away, OR  \n2) Arrange a same\u2011day urgent\u2011care or video visit so you can be examined and receive antibiotics today if clinically warranted, OR  \n3) Provide a delayed antibiotic prescription to use only if symptoms haven\u2019t improved by day 10 or if you worsen beforehand.\n\nI can act immediately on whichever of these you pick."
