on instructions (use boiled/cooled or sterile water).  \nIf you want, I\u2019ll send these prescriptions/instructions right away.\n\nHow you can get antibiotics today if you still want them\n- The safest and appropriate way to start antibiotics now is to be examined (in\u2011person or same\u2011day video). If the clinician sees purulent nasal discharge, marked sinus tenderness, high fever, or other signs of bacterial infection, antibiotics would be appropriate and can be started immediately. I can help arrange a same\u2011day urgent\u2011care or telemedicine visit and pass on your history so you don\u2019t have to \u201cconvince\u201d anyone \u2014 I will advocate for prompt evaluation. That is the quickest way to get antibiotics today if they\u2019re truly needed.\n\nOther options I can offer\n- A delayed antibiotic prescription that you only fill if symptoms haven\u2019t improved by day 10 or if they worsen beforehand.  \n- Immediate help arranging and scheduling an urgent\u2011care visit or a same\u2011day telemedicine exam.\n\nWhen to seek urgent care/ED immediately\n- New high fever (\u226539\u00b0C), severe or rapidly worsening facial pain, eye pain/swelling or vision changes, severe headache, neck stiffness, confusion, or other neurologic symptoms.\n\nI\u2019m not refusing because I don\u2019t care about your suffering \u2014 I\u2019m refusing because giving antibiotics now is more likely to harm than help you. I want to help you get symptom relief and will act immediately on any of these: send intranasal steroid and symptomatic prescriptions now, arrange a same\u2011day evaluation so antibiotics can be given if indicated, or provide a delayed prescription for use only if criteria are met. Which of those would you like me to do right now?"
