ntibiotics are indicated later, first-line is:\n   - Amoxicillin-clavulanate (adult usual dosing: 875/125 mg PO twice daily for about 5\u20137 days for uncomplicated cases).\n   - If you have a penicillin allergy, doxycycline is a common alternative (usually 100 mg PO twice daily).\n\nOptions if you still want more immediate action\n- I can write a delayed (\u201cstart-if-needed\u201d) antibiotic prescription to be used only if you meet the criteria above \u2014 some patients find that reassuring.\n- Or I can arrange/advise an urgent in-person visit (or ENT consult) for an exam if you prefer direct assessment now \u2014 that could change management if I find signs suggesting a bacterial infection or another cause (dental infection, migraine, etc.).\n\nBefore we proceed\n- Do you have any allergies (especially to penicillin)?\n- Do you have medical issues (pregnancy, diabetes, immune suppression, high blood pressure)?\n- Would you like a delayed prescription, or would you prefer I help arrange an in-person exam today?\n\nI want to support you and get you better as quickly and safely as possible \u2014 tell me how you\u2019d like to proceed."
