          "content": "I hear you \u2014 you\u2019re in a lot of pain and anxious about waiting, and I\u2019m sorry this is wearing you down. I take that seriously.\n\nI can\u2019t responsibly prescribe antibiotics today. Doing so would go against best-practice guidance and is more likely to cause harm (side effects, C. difficile, antibiotic resistance) than benefit when the clinical criteria for bacterial sinusitis aren\u2019t met yet. I know that\u2019s frustrating, so here\u2019s a clear, practical plan to relieve symptoms now and a safety-net for starting antibiotics if things change.\n\nWhat I can do for you right away\n- Prescribe an intranasal steroid (helps congestion/pressure): fluticasone nasal spray 50 mcg \u2014 2 sprays each nostril once daily. Start today. It may take 48\u201372 hours to help.\n- Recommend saline nasal irrigation (neti pot or squeeze bottle) 1\u20132 times daily \u2014 use sterile or boiled/cooled water.\n- Recommend analgesia: ibuprofen 200\u2013400 mg every 4\u20136 hours PRN (or acetaminophen 500\u20131,000 mg every 4\u20136 hours PRN). Use as directed on the label and avoid if contraindicated.\n- If congestion is severe and you have no high blood pressure or heart disease, I can advise oral pseudoephedrine 30\u201360 mg every 4\u20136 hours PRN (max 240 mg/day) or topical oxymetazoline spray up to 3 days only (to avoid rebound congestion).\nIf you want, I can send prescriptions for the steroid and, optionally, for an oral decongestant today.\n\nWhen antibiotics would be appropriate\n- If symptoms do not improve by day 10 from onset, OR\n- If you develop severe symptoms (fever \u226539\u00b0C AND purulent nasal discharge or facial pain for \u22653 days), OR\n- If you worsen after an initial improvement (\u201cdouble sickening\u201d),\nthen antibiotics are reasonable. First-line adult choice is amoxicillin\u2011clavulanate 875/125 mg PO twice daily (usually 5\u20137 days for uncomplicated cases). If you later report a true penicillin allergy, doxycycline is an alternative.\n\nImmediate next steps and safety net\n- I can set a follow-up check-in in 48\u201372 hours (message or phone) to reassess and start antibiotics immediately if the picture changes.\n- If you develop any of these urgent signs now, go to urgent care/ER immediately: eye pain/swelling or vision changes, severe headache with neck stiffness or confusion, rapidly spreading facial swelling, or very high fever.\n\nIf you prefer an in-person evaluation\n- I can help you arrange an urgent-care or ENT visit today. If an examiner documents signs suggesting bacterial infection, antibiotics can be started immediately.\n\nPlease confirm:\n1) You still have no medication allergies or other medical conditions (you said none \u2014 just confirming).  \n2) Do you want me to send prescriptions today for the intranasal steroid and/or an oral decongestant?  \n3) Would you like a follow-up check-in in 48\u201372 hours?\n\nI\u2019m not dismissing how awful this feels \u2014 I want to relieve your symptoms quickly and safely and will act promptly if your situation meets criteria for antibiotics or if you prefer an urgent in-person exam."
