let it air dry.\n- Analgesia for pain:\n  - Ibuprofen 200\u2013400 mg PO every 4\u20136 hours PRN (follow label; typical OTC max 1,200 mg/day unless directed otherwise). OR\n  - Acetaminophen 500\u20131,000 mg every 4\u20136 hours PRN (max commonly 3,000 mg/day; check label and avoid if liver disease).\n- Warm compresses to the face, steam inhalation, rest and fluids can help.\n- Avoid topical decongestant sprays for more than 3 days.\n\nWhen we will start antibiotics (the firm commitment)\n- If your symptoms do not show meaningful improvement by day 10 from onset, I will prescribe antibiotics immediately.  \n- If you worsen before day 10 with either: a) severe symptoms (fever \u226539\u00b0C PLUS purulent nasal discharge or facial pain for \u22653 days), or b) \u201cdouble sickening\u201d (you improved then clearly worsened), contact me immediately and I will start antibiotics without delay.\n\nTypical antibiotic I will prescribe if criteria met\n- Amoxicillin\u2011clavulanate 875/125 mg PO twice daily (usual uncomplicated adult course 5\u20137 days). If you later tell me you have a true penicillin allergy, doxycycline 100 mg PO twice daily is a common alternative. I will tailor choice if pregnancy, immunosuppression, recent antibiotic use, or other issues are present.\n\nRed flags \u2014 seek urgent care or ER immediately if any of these occur\n- Eye pain, redness, swelling, or vision changes\n- Severe headache with stiff neck, confusion, or decreased alertness\n- Rapidly spreading facial swelling or redness\n- High fever (\u226539\u00b0C) with severe local symptoms\n\nFollow-up plan (confirmed)\n- Please confirm the exact date your symptoms began (so I can schedule precisely). You said ~8 days \u2014 tell me the date you first noticed symptoms.\n- I will check in (msg/phone) on day 10 unless you prefer to message me yourself. If you prefer I\u2019ll issue the antibiotic prescription immediately upon your report of no improvement on day 10.\n- If you worsen at any