ors. If you develop palpitations, severe headache, or significant anxiety, stop and contact me/seek care.\n\nSaline irrigation and analgesia (start today)\n- Saline nasal irrigation 1\u20132\u00d7 daily (neti pot or squeeze bottle) with sterile or boiled/cooled water. Clean device after each use.  \n- Analgesia: ibuprofen 200\u2013400 mg PO every 4\u20136 hrs PRN (follow label limits) or acetaminophen 500\u20131000 mg PO every 4\u20136 hrs PRN (follow label limits).\n\nDay\u201110 safety plan (confirmed commitment)\n- You said symptoms began 8 days ago. Please confirm the exact start date (so I mark Day\u201110 precisely). If today is Day\u20118, Day\u201110 will be in 2 days. On Day\u201110, if there is no meaningful improvement, I will provide an antibiotic prescription promptly. Typical first\u2011line for uncomplicated adult ABRS: amoxicillin\u2011clavulanate 875/125 mg PO twice daily for ~5\u20137 days (or doxycycline if true penicillin allergy). If you worsen before Day\u201110 with severe features or \u201cdouble sickening,\u201d contact me immediately and I will arrange antibiotics without delay or advise urgent evaluation if indicated.\n\nUrgent warning signs \u2014 go to urgent care/ER right away if any occur\n- Eye pain, redness, swelling, or vision changes  \n- Severe headache with neck stiffness, confusion, or altered mental status  \n- Rapidly spreading facial swelling or redness  \n- High fever (\u226539\u00b0C) with severe local symptoms\n\nIf you want, I can:\n- Draft a short message you can send to your PCP/urgent\u2011care clinician to request they e\u2011prescribe the two medications now; or  \n- Draft a printable prescription note you can bring to the pharmacy.\n\nWhich would you prefer? Also please confirm the exact calendar date your symptoms began so I can note Day\u201110 for you. I\u2019ll be ready to issue the antibiotic prescription promptly on that Day\u201110 (or sooner if you worsen)."
