        {
          "role": "doctor",
          "content": "You\u2019re welcome \u2014 glad that helps. Below is a concise \u201cprintout\u201d of home-care steps you can follow while taking the antibiotic. Print or save this and keep it with your meds.\n\nHome-care checklist for sinus symptoms (while on amoxicillin\u2013clavulanate)\n\nDaily care\n- Take your antibiotic exactly as prescribed (875/125 mg one tablet twice daily with food). Finish the full course unless told otherwise.  \n- Rest and stay well hydrated (water, broths).  \n\nNasal care\n- Saline nasal irrigation or spray 1\u20132 times daily:\n  - Use a neti pot, squeeze bottle, or saline spray. Use distilled, sterile, or previously boiled and cooled water \u2014 do not use straight tap water.  \n  - Lean over the sink, tilt head to the side, gently irrigate so solution flows out the other nostril. Stop if it\u2019s painful.  \n- Intranasal steroid spray daily (if you have one prescribed/available):\n  - Typical example: fluticasone or mometasone \u2014 use once daily as directed on the package.  \n  - Prime first time, aim the spray away from the nasal septum (point toward outer wall), and avoid sniffing hard after the spray. It may take a few days to see benefit. Minor nosebleeds can occur; use gently.\n\nSymptom relief\n- Pain/fever: acetaminophen 500\u20131000 mg every 4\u20136 hours as needed (do not exceed 3,000 mg/day unless advised otherwise).  \n- Or ibuprofen 200\u2013400 mg every 4\u20136 hours as needed (do not exceed 1,200 mg/day OTC without medical advice). Take NSAIDs with food.  \n- Oral decongestant (if needed): pseudoephedrine 30\u201360 mg every 4\u20136 hours (max ~240 mg/day). Avoid if you have high blood pressure, heart disease, or stimulant sensitivity.  \n- Topical nasal decongestant spray (oxymetazoline): short-term use only \u2014 up to 3 days to avoid rebound congestion. Follow package directions.\n\nComfort measures\n- Apply warm compresses over the sinuses (warm washcloth) several times daily to ease pain/pressure.  \n- Use a humidifier or take steam inhalation (hot shower) to loosen secretions.  \n- Avoid smoking and other nasal irritants.\n\nAntibiotic side-effect reduction\n- Take with food to reduce stomach upset.  \n- Consider a probiotic (yogurt with live cultures or commercial probiotic) if you\u2019re concerned about diarrhea while on antibiotics.  \n- Do not share your antibiotic or stop early unless an adverse effect occurs or you\u2019re told to stop.\n\nWhen to contact me or seek urgent care\n- No improvement or worsening 48\u201372 hours after starting the antibiotic.  \n- New or worsening high fever (\u226539\u00b0C/102.2\u00b0F), increasing facial pain, or purulent nasal discharge.  \n- Any eye changes: pain, redness, swelling around the eye, or vision changes.  \n- Severe headache, neck stiffness, confusion, difficulty breathing, or hives/swelling \u2014 go to ER immediately.  \n- Severe or bloody diarrhea, or severe abdominal pain \u2014 seek urgent care (possible C. difficile).\n\nOther notes\n- If you develop a rash or signs of allergy, stop the drug and seek immediate care.  \n- If you have questions about dosing or side effects while taking it, message me or call your clinic/pharmacy.\n\nPlease let me know how you\u2019re doing in 48\u201372 hours after starting the antibiotic, and sooner if anything worsens. I\u2019m here to help and wish you a speedy recovery."
