trouble breathing.\n- If you take warfarin or other interacting meds, your clinician should review interactions.\n- If symptoms worsen (high fever \u226539\u00b0C), new swelling/redness around an eye, vision changes, severe facial pain, neck stiffness, confusion \u2014 go to urgent care or ER immediately.\n- Follow-up: check in with your clinician in 48\u201372 hours to reassess; if no improvement by day 10, or if you worsen, further evaluation may be needed.\n\nSample message you can copy to your clinician or urgent-care/telehealth provider\n(Short, factual request)\n\u201cHi \u2014 I\u2019m a 35-year-old with 8 days of progressively worse facial pressure/pressure and nasal congestion (mostly clear/white discharge), no fever, no chronic sinus disease, no recent antibiotics, and no drug allergies. My symptoms have steadily worsened and I\u2019m very symptomatic despite supportive measures. I would like to start an antibiotic after shared-decision discussion. I\u2019m requesting amoxicillin\u2013clavulanate 875/125 mg PO twice daily for 7 days (or an alternative if you prefer). Please let me know if you agree or if you recommend a different plan. I will follow up in 48\u201372 hours or sooner if I worsen.\u201d\n\nIf you want, I can tailor that message to be shorter or to include more medical detail for a telehealth note. I\u2019m also happy to walk through the pros/cons again or support you in contacting a clinician now. Which would you prefer?"
