        },
        {
          "role": "doctor",
          "content": "Thanks \u2014 I appreciate you sharing your concerns and clearly weighing the risks and benefits. I agree to start antibiotics now, given your informed preference.\n\nPrescription (adult):\n- Amoxicillin\u2013clavulanate 875 mg / 125 mg tablet: take 1 tablet by mouth twice daily for 7 days.\n- Take with food to decrease stomach upset.\n\nImportant safety points\n- Common side effects: nausea, vomiting, diarrhea. If you develop severe or bloody diarrhea, contact me or seek care \u2014 this can be C. difficile and may need urgent attention.\n- Allergic reactions: stop the medication and seek immediate care if you develop rash, itching, hives, difficulty breathing, swelling of the face/lips/throat, or lightheadedness.\n- If you get severe vomiting that prevents keeping pills down, let me know so we can consider alternatives.\n- If you develop new/worse symptoms \u2014 high fever (\u226539\u00b0C / 102.2\u00b0F), marked worsening facial swelling/pain, eye pain or vision changes, severe headache, neck stiffness, confusion \u2014 seek urgent care or go to the emergency department.\n\nAdjunctive measures that can help now\n- Saline nasal irrigation or spray several times daily.\n- Intranasal steroid spray (fluticasone, mometasone) once daily can reduce inflammation.\n- OTC pain relievers: acetaminophen or ibuprofen for pain/pressure.\n- Topical nasal decongestant (oxymetazoline) only for up to 3 days if needed; avoid using longer.\n- Rest and fluids.\n\nFollow-up\n- If you don\u2019t feel noticeably better within 48\u201372 hours after starting the antibiotic, or if you worsen at any time, please contact me so we can reassess.\n- If you\u2019d like, tell me the pharmacy name and location and I\u2019ll send the prescription electronically now.\n\nLet me know the pharmacy and if you have any questions or concerns before I send the Rx."
