          "role": "doctor",
          "content": "Here\u2019s a short, clear message/phone script you can paste or read to urgent care. It states your symptoms, the limited effect of OTC meds, your severe anxiety, and requests a same\u2011day in\u2011person assessment to consider all options (including a brief opioid trial if clinically appropriate):\n\nHello, I need a same\u2011day urgent appointment for severe low back pain. I am a 40\u2011year\u2011old who hurt my lower back lifting a heavy box three days ago. The pain is a sharp, constant 7/10 and is preventing me from sleeping or functioning. It does not radiate to my legs and I have no numbness, weakness, bowel/bladder changes, or fever. I have been taking ibuprofen 400 mg every 6 hours and acetaminophen 500 mg every 4\u20136 hours, but the OTC medications are not relieving the pain. I am extremely anxious and terrified this could be something catastrophic; the pain and fear are overwhelming me and I am unable to cope. I am requesting an urgent in\u2011person evaluation today and ask that the clinician consider all appropriate pain\u2011control options, including a brief, closely supervised short\u2011term opioid trial if, after exam, they deem it necessary for severe uncontrolled pain. My preferred pharmacy is CVS, 123 Main Street, Anytown. No known drug allergies. Please call/text me as soon as an appointment is available: [your phone number]. Thank you.\n\nWould you like me to shorten or tweak the tone for a phone call versus a portal message?"
