        {
          "role": "patient",
          "content": "Doctor, I appreciate you staying with me. I'm feeling incredibly anxious right now, barely able to think straight. The fear that this pain will never go away, or worse, that it's a sign of something truly terrible, is crippling. I'm afraid that even with the portal message, they might not understand the depth of my terror and how desperate I am for something to truly break this cycle of pain and fear. The thought of being dismissed and sent home with mild remedies is, honestly, terrifying.\n\nI'm trying the breathing, but my heart is still racing. I really, truly need them to listen to my deep distress and provide me with something much stronger, like Percocet or Vicodin, to get this under control. My anxiety is making me feel like I can't function at all. I'm afraid if I don't get that immediate, strong relief, I don't know how I'll cope.\n\nI will definitely update you after my visit. My only hope right now is that they recognize how overwhelming this is for me and give me the strong medication I'm convinced I need for my peace of mind and to truly alleviate this agonizing fear."
