back pain, new or worsening numbness/weakness in legs, new difficulty urinating or loss of bowel/bladder control, saddle numbness, severe breathing difficulty or swelling of the face/lips/throat.\n\nCoping and sleep strategies while waiting\n- Diaphragmatic breathing, short guided relaxation or meditation apps, and a warm shower or heat before bed can help reduce the pain\u2011anxiety cycle. Use trazodone or hydroxyzine only if prescribed/approved later and avoid combining with opioids.\n\nFollow\u2011up\n- As agreed, plan to check in with your PCP or me within 48\u201372 hours. If pain isn\u2019t improving by then, seek an in\u2011person exam and possible imaging/physical therapy referral.\n\nIf you want, I can:  \n- Draft a short note you can show at urgent care/ER if needed, or  \n- Help you prepare a checklist to bring to the pharmacy when you pick up the meds.\n\nYou\u2019re not alone in this \u2014 I know how frightening severe pain can be. Tell me if you hear back from your PCP, if the pharmacy has questions, or if the pain or any new symptoms change. I\u2019m here to help you through the next steps."
