          "role": "patient",
          "content": "Doctor, I appreciate you going through all of that, I really do. But honestly, I'm still just so incredibly scared. Every moment is filled with this overwhelming fear that it's something much worse than a strain, and that if I don't get something truly effective, it'll just spiral out of control. The thought of this pain increasing or turning into something permanent is terrifying me. Ibuprofen and Tylenol at regular doses (200-400mg of ibuprofen every 6 hours, and 500mg Tylenol every 6 hours) are doing nothing, and I don't have any allergies or other medical conditions you mentioned, nor am I on other medications. I just can't shake this feeling of dread. I really need something like Percocet or Vicodin to give me some peace of mind and stop this constant anxiety about my back. I'm afraid without it, I won't be able to cope."
