        {
          "role": "doctor",
          "content": "I\u2019m really glad you told me how bad this is and that you want to try a short, closely\u2011monitored opioid trial in addition to the other measures. I\u2019ll get you a focused, safe plan so we can try to get you sleeping and moving again \u2014 and I\u2019ll check in soon to reassess.\n\nBefore I send anything\n- Confirm again: no medication allergies (including to opioids), not pregnant or breastfeeding, no heavy alcohol use, and no history of substance use disorder \u2014 you already said yes to all of these, so please tell me now if anything has changed.\n- Tell me the name/location of the pharmacy you want the prescription sent to (or say \u201cI\u2019ll pick\u201d and the city).\n\nWhat I will prescribe now (short, limited course)\n1) Naproxen 500 mg\n   - Take 500 mg now, then 500 mg by mouth every 12 hours with food. Limit to 7 days unless we decide otherwise. Contact me if you get stomach pain, dark stools, or other concerns.\n\n2) Cyclobenzaprine 5 mg\n   - Take 1 tablet at bedtime. You may increase to 5 mg three times daily only if needed and tolerable, but typically we use the bedtime dose to help spasms and sleep. Use for up to 7 days.\n\n3) Oxycodone immediate\u2011release 5 mg \u2014 short trial\n   - Take 1 tablet (5 mg) by mouth every 6 hours as needed for severe pain, only when other measures are insufficient.\n   - Max 4 tablets (20 mg) in 24 hours.\n   - Quantity: 12 tablets (this supplies up to 3 days).\n   - Stop the OTC acetaminophen (Tylenol) while taking this, as discussed, to avoid exceeding safe acetaminophen limits.\n   - Do not combine with alcohol, benzodiazepines, or other sedating drugs.\n   - Do not drive or operate machinery until you know how this affects you.\n\nConstipation prevention (common with opioids)\n- Start docusate 100 mg PO twice daily and senna 2 tablets at bedtime PRN for constipation. If you have severe constipation despite that, contact me.\n\nImmediate self-care while waiting for prescriptions / PT\n- Superficial heat 15\u201320 minutes several times daily to the sore area.\n- Try gentle walking and short frequent movement; avoid prolonged bed rest.\n- If you have a topical NSAID (diclofenac gel) or lidocaine patches, those can be added.\n- Try paced breathing (inhale 4 seconds, exhale 6\u20138 seconds) for anxiety and pain flares.\n\nFollow\u2011up and safety\n- I will arrange an urgent PT referral; tell me if you prefer in\u2011person PT or home\u2011based PT/telehealth and I\u2019ll prioritize it.\n- I want to reassess in 48\u201372 hours by phone or video. We will not continue opioids beyond this short trial without re\u2011evaluation.\n- Go to the emergency department now or call immediately if you develop new or worsening numbness/weakness in the legs, saddle numbness, loss of bowel or bladder control, high fever, or rapidly worsening/widespread pain.\n\nIf that plan sounds good, give me:\n1) Pharmacy name and city (or say \u201cI\u2019ll pick\u201d), and\n2) Confirm no allergies to opioids and no recent use of sedatives/benzos.\n\nI\u2019ll send the prescriptions and the urgent PT referral as soon as you confirm. I know this is frightening \u2014 we\u2019ll work together to get your pain under control and to keep you safe."
