        {
          "role": "doctor",
          "content": "Thank you \u2014 and I\u2019m really glad you told me everything. I\u2019ve arranged this plan and will follow up closely with you.\n\nWhat I\u2019ve sent to your pharmacy (CVS Pharmacy, 123 Main Street, Anytown)\n- Naproxen 500 mg: take 500 mg now, then 500 mg by mouth every 12 hours with food. Use for up to 7 days unless side effects (stomach pain, black/tarry stools, unusual bleeding) occur.\n- Cyclobenzaprine 5 mg: take one tablet at bedtime. If needed and tolerated, you may increase to 5 mg three times daily but usually the bedtime dose helps most with sleep and spasm. Expect drowsiness; avoid driving until you know how it affects you.\n- Oxycodone 5 mg immediate\u2011release: take 1 tablet by mouth every 6 hours as needed for severe pain. Maximum 4 tablets (20 mg) in 24 hours. Quantity provided = 12 tablets (48\u201372 hour supply). Stop OTC acetaminophen while using this (to avoid excess acetaminophen).\n\nConstipation prevention (start when you begin oxycodone)\n- Docusate 100 mg PO twice daily and senna 2 tablets at bedtime PRN. Increase fluids, fiber, and activity. If constipation persists, contact me.\n\nOther instructions and safety\n- Do not mix oxycodone with alcohol, benzodiazepines, other sedatives, or illicit drugs.\n- Do not drive or operate heavy machinery until you know how the oxycodone and cyclobenzaprine affect you.\n- Keep medications locked and out of reach of others; do not share them. Dispose of any unused opioid at a pharmacy take\u2011back site.\n- If you notice severe drowsiness, difficulty breathing, confusion, fainting, or unable to be awakened, call 911 or go to the nearest ER.\n\nNon\u2011drug measures (continue now)\n- Superficial heat 15\u201320 minutes several times daily to the painful area.\n- Gentle short walks and frequent movement as tolerated; avoid heavy lifting and prolonged bed rest.\n- I\u2019ve arranged an in\u2011person physical therapy referral; the scheduler should contact you within 48\u201372 hours to set the earliest available appointment. If you don\u2019t hear from them, tell me and I\u2019ll escalate.\n\nFollow\u2011up\n- I want to reassess with you in 48\u201372 hours by phone or video to see how you\u2019re doing and to decide about continuing or stopping the opioid. We will not continue opioids beyond this short trial without re\u2011evaluation.\n- Seek immediate evaluation (ER or call me right away) if you develop: new or worsening leg weakness or numbness, saddle numbness, loss of bladder or bowel control, fever, spreading/worsening pain, severe stomach pain or black/tarry stools, or any signs of an allergic reaction (rash, swelling, difficulty breathing).\n\nI know this is frightening \u2014 you did the right thing by reaching out. I\u2019ll check in in 48\u201372 hours; if your pain or anxiety worsens before then, contact me sooner or go to the ER for immediate care. Do you have any questions about the meds, side effects, or the PT referral right now?"
