        {
          "role": "doctor",
          "content": "Here\u2019s a short message you can copy/paste into your patient portal or send to your PCP/urgent care clinician. It includes the exact prescription wording requested, pharmacy details, and urgent language.\n\nSubject: Urgent: severe acute low back pain \u2014 request for short opioid bridge, bowel regimen, and expedited PT referral\n\nHello \u2014 this is Jane Doe, DOB 01/01/1983. I injured my lower back 3 days ago while lifting a heavy box. I have severe, constant pain rated ~7/10 that is incapacitating and preventing sleep and function. I have no fever, no falls, no bowel/bladder dysfunction, and no leg weakness or numbness.\n\nI\u2019ve been taking ibuprofen 400 mg every 6 hours and acetaminophen 500 mg about 4\u20135 times/day (\u22482,000\u20132,500 mg/day) with no meaningful relief. I would like to request an urgent, short opioid bridge and constipation prevention plus an expedited outpatient PT referral so I can sleep and begin recovery.\n\nRequested prescriptions (please e-prescribe to CVS on Main Street, Anytown, USA \u2014 I consent to e-prescribing):\n1) Oxycodone IR 5 mg tablets\n   - Sig: take 1 tablet PO every 4\u20136 hours PRN for severe pain; max 6 tablets/day (30 mg/day)\n   - Dispense: 10 tablets (3\u2011day supply)\n   - No refills\n   - Indication: acute severe mechanical low back pain after lifting\n\n(Please note I am currently taking acetaminophen separately; I prefer an opioid without acetaminophen. If you prescribe a product that contains acetaminophen, I will stop my separate acetaminophen immediately to avoid overdose.)\n\n2) Constipation prevention\n   - Docusate sodium 100 mg PO twice daily\n   - Senna (sennosides) 8.6 mg PO at bedtime PRN\n\n3) Expedited outpatient physical therapy referral\n   - Indication: acute low back pain; request same\u2011week evaluation for hands\u2011on care, mobility training, and supervised therapeutic exercises\n\nAdditional requests/notes\n- Please schedule a follow\u2011up phone or portal check in 48\u201372 hours to reassess pain and discontinue opioid as soon as possible.\n- I understand safety instructions (no alcohol, no benzodiazepines/sedatives while taking opioid; avoid driving until effects known).\n- If you prefer to discuss alternatives before prescribing, please contact me via portal/phone (contact info on file).\n\nThank you \u2014 I appreciate prompt help as this is currently incapacitating and preventing sleep."
