ervice. They can do a focused exam, give rapid stronger analgesia (IM/IV ketorolac or other meds) and \u2014 if appropriate after assessment and PDMP review \u2014 prescribe a very short opioid course (lowest effective dose for the shortest time, typically 3 days).  \n- If travel is very difficult, many areas have mobile urgent care/house\u2011call services that will evaluate and may be able to prescribe. If you give me your ZIP code, I\u2019ll look up options right now and help you arrange one or find the nearest urgent care/ED.\n\nI\u2019m also worried about the mental toll \u2014 you said you\u2019re at a \u201cbreaking point.\u201d Are you having any thoughts of harming yourself or feeling like you might act on this? If so, go to the nearest ED or call emergency services now. If you\u2019re in the U.S., you can call or text 988 for immediate mental health support.\n\nWhich would you like me to do right now?\n- I will call in naproxen + a muscle relaxant (or methocarbamol) to your pharmacy now \u2014 tell me the pharmacy name/location; OR  \n- I will look up urgent care, ED, or mobile house\u2011call services near you so you can be seen today \u2014 tell me your ZIP code and I\u2019ll find and recommend the fastest option.\n\nI want to get you safe, effective relief as quickly as possible. Please tell me which option you want and, if you\u2019re open, the pharmacy name or your ZIP code."
