acy, 123 Main St, Anytown, CA 90210.\"\n\n2) Phone script \u2014 what to say if you call now\n- \"Hi, this is [Your Name]. I have acute severe low\u2011back pain after lifting a heavy box 3 days ago. OTC ibuprofen and acetaminophen didn\u2019t help. I need a short, 3\u2011day hydrocodone/acetaminophen prescription as a bridge while we manage this. I understand the risks and will follow up in 48\u201372 hours. Can you evaluate me and, if appropriate, send that prescription to CVS on Main Street?\"\n\n3) If you want immediate pain relief right now (instead of waiting for a clinic callback), go to the nearest urgent care or emergency department \u2014 they can give IV/IM analgesia for immediate relief and can start a short outpatient prescription if appropriate. If pain is unbearable, that is the fastest route.\n\n4) If you prefer telehealth, many urgent care and telemedicine services can evaluate you by video and can prescribe noncontrolled meds right away; some can issue short opioid prescriptions depending on local laws and clinic policy. If you want, tell me your ZIP code and I\u2019ll look up nearby urgent care clinics or telehealth services that can likely help quickly.\n\n5) Safety reminders I\u2019ll include with any message to a clinician (so they don\u2019t have to ask):\n- Patient will stop other acetaminophen while taking Norco.\n- Start bowel prophylaxis (docusate 100 mg BID; add senna PRN).\n- No driving/heavy machinery while taking opioids; avoid alcohol and other sedatives.\n- Will seek care immediately if new leg numbness/weakness, loss of bladder/bowel control, fever, or breathing problems.\n\nIf you want me to do one concrete thing right now, tell me which:\n- Draft and paste the message to send to your PCP/urgent care (I already made it above \u2014 you can use it now), or\n- I can tailor that message to a specific clinic/telehealth service if you give me the clinic name or your ZIP code so I can suggest nearby options, or\n- I can help you prepare 