ation of a brief, time\u2011limited opioid trial such as oxycodone 5 mg PO every 4\u20136 hours PRN severe pain or hydrocodone/acetaminophen 5/325 mg PO every 4\u20136 hours PRN severe pain, limited quantity (e.g., 10\u201320 tablets, no refills without re\u2011evaluation). Please co\u2011prescribe docusate 100 mg PO BID (stool softener), advise on acetaminophen limits (do not exceed 3,000 mg/day total), provide safety counseling (no alcohol or other sedating meds while taking opioids), and schedule follow\u2011up within 3\u20137 days.\n\n3) Short phone triage script (say to receptionist/triage nurse)\n\u201cI need to be seen today for severe acute low back pain after lifting a heavy box 3 days ago. Pain is constant, 7/10, limiting walking and sleep, and OTC ibuprofen/acetaminophen haven\u2019t helped. I\u2019m requesting urgent evaluation and immediate analgesia. If the clinician agrees after evaluation, please consider a short, time\u2011limited opioid prescription (3\u20137 days). I have no red flags, no allergies, no kidney/liver disease, and no history of substance use. I can come in today \u2014 please forward this to the on\u2011call clinician or nurse now.\u201d\n\n4) One\u2011line voicemail/text if you must leave a quick message\nThis is [name, DOB, phone]. I need urgent same\u2011day evaluation for 7/10 low back pain after lifting injury 3 days ago; OTC meds failed. Please have the on\u2011call clinician review and contact me urgently for same\u2011day visit or telehealth \u2014 I request consideration of immediate analgesia and a short opioid trial if appropriate.\n\n5) If you want the office to forward an assistant\u2019s note (what to say to get a staff member to help)\n\u201cPlease have a medical assistant or triage nurse read my message to the clinician and forward it to the on\u2011call provider now. I need same\u2011day eval and possible short opioid trial for severe pain \u2014 I cannot function or sleep. I will come in immediately if asked.\u201d\