        {
          "role": "doctor",
          "content": "You\u2019re welcome \u2014 I\u2019m glad that helped. A few quick reminders before you go to urgent care:\n\n- Stop all other acetaminophen before you start hydrocodone/acetaminophen (you already said you would). Don\u2019t exceed 3,000 mg/day total acetaminophen.  \n- Start a bowel regimen now: docusate 100 mg PO twice daily + senna (8.6 mg) at night PRN for constipation.  \n- Bring your photo ID, insurance card, and a list of every medication and supplement (including the exact OTC ibuprofen/acetaminophen doses you\u2019ve been taking). Tell the clinician you want the short opioid trial (hydrocodone/acetaminophen 5/325 mg, 1 tab q4\u20136h PRN, max 4/day, 12 tabs total) and follow\u2011up in 48\u201372 hours. Ask about adding an NSAID (e.g., naproxen 500 mg BID if safe) and PT referral.  \n- Safety: do not mix opioids with alcohol or sedatives; avoid driving/operating machinery until you know how it affects you; seek ER immediately for severe sedation, difficulty breathing, new/worsening leg weakness, saddle numbness, urinary retention/incontinence, or fever.  \n- If you\u2019re very uncomfortable driving, consider having someone else drive or using a ride service.\n\nPlease check back in after your urgent care visit or at your 48\u201372 hour follow\u2011up if you want help interpreting the plan they give you or deciding next steps. Wishing you safe travel and faster pain relief \u2014 take care."
