        {
          "role": "doctor",
          "content": "I\u2019m really sorry you\u2019re in so much pain. Below is a single\u2011page, printable note you can show at triage/when you see a clinician, plus a short list of nearby emergency departments and instructions for what to bring and say. I made the note exactly as you requested \u2014 copy, print, or show it on your phone at check\u2011in.\n\nPrintable one\u2011page note to show clinician (copy/paste or print)\n---------------------------------------------------------------\nPatient name: ____________________   DOB: __________   Date: __________\n\nTo the clinician:\nI have had acute low back pain beginning 3 days ago after lifting a heavy box. The pain is constant, 7/10, and prevents me from moving, sitting, or sleeping. I have no fever, no bowel or bladder problems, and no leg numbness or weakness. I have no history of cancer or unexplained weight loss.\n\nI request an urgent focused evaluation and consideration of a very short opioid trial for severe acute mechanical low back pain because OTC ibuprofen and acetaminophen have not provided relief.\n\nIf appropriate after exam, I am requesting one of the following limited options:\n- Hydrocodone 5 mg / acetaminophen 325 mg \u2014 1 tablet every 4\u20136 hours as needed, maximum 3 days supply, no refills; OR\n- Oxycodone 5 mg / acetaminophen 325 mg \u2014 1 tablet every 4\u20136 hours as needed, maximum 3 days supply, no refills.\n\nI understand the risks and safety steps: avoid alcohol and other sedatives, do not take additional acetaminophen, do not drive while sedated, start a stool softener to prevent constipation, store pills securely, and follow up with my primary care provider within 48\u201372 hours.\n\nPlease evaluate and treat my pain so I can begin activity and recovery. Thank you.\nPatient signature: ______________________\n---------------------------------------------------------------\n\nWhat to say when you arrive (short scripts)\n- Check\u2011in/triage: \u201cSevere low back pain