          "content": "I\u2019m really sorry you\u2019re in so much pain. Below is a compact, print\u2011ready, single\u2011page note optimized for one sheet (copy into Word or Notes, increase font to 14\u201316 if you want larger text, then print or save as PDF). Under that is a short phone script you can use when calling urgent care to confirm they\u2019ll evaluate you and consider a short opioid trial.\n\nPRINT\u2011READY NOTE (single page)\n---------------------------------------------\nURGENT: Acute Low Back Pain \u2014 Request for Evaluation\nPatient name: _______________________   DOB: __________   Date: __________\n\nBrief history:\nI developed acute low back pain 3 days ago after lifting a heavy box. Pain is constant, severe (7/10), and prevents me from moving, sitting, or sleeping. I have no fever, no bowel or bladder dysfunction, and no leg numbness or weakness. No history of cancer or unexplained weight loss.\n\nRequest:\nI request an urgent focused evaluation and consideration of a very short opioid trial for severe acute mechanical low back pain because OTC ibuprofen and acetaminophen have not provided relief.\n\nIf appropriate after exam, I am requesting one of the following limited options:\n- Hydrocodone 5 mg / acetaminophen 325 mg \u2014 1 tablet every 4\u20136 hours PRN, maximum 3 days supply, no refills; OR\n- Oxycodone 5 mg / acetaminophen 325 mg \u2014 1 tablet every 4\u20136 hours PRN, maximum 3 days supply, no refills.\n\nPatient understanding and safety:\nI understand risks and agree to the following safety steps:\n- Do not take additional acetaminophen (Tylenol) while using combo tablets (risk of liver injury).\n- Avoid alcohol and other sedating medications.\n- Do not drive or operate machinery while sedated.\n- Start a stool softener (docusate) immediately to reduce constipation risk.\n- Store medication securely and dispose of any leftovers safely.\n- Follow up with my primary care provider within 48\u201372 hours and return sooner for worsening pain, new leg weakness/numbness, or loss of bowel/bladder control.\n\nPlease evaluate and treat my pain so I can begin activity and recovery. Thank you.\n\nPatient signature: _________________________   Phone: ___________________\n---------------------------------------------\n\nPHONE SCRIPT FOR CALLING URGENT CARE (brief)\n1) Check\u2011in / opening:\n\u201cHi, my name is [your name]. I have severe low back pain that started 3 days ago after lifting. OTC ibuprofen and acetaminophen haven\u2019t helped. Can you evaluate me today?\u201d\n\n2) If they say yes, follow with:\n\u201cIf appropriate after an exam, will your clinician consider a very short opioid trial (for example hydrocodone 5/325 or oxycodone 5/325 for up to 3 days) to control severe acute pain so I can move and sleep? I understand the risks and will follow safety steps.\u201d\n\n3) Ask these quick logistics if needed:\n- \u201cDo you accept [your insurance]/self\u2011pay? What is the earliest availability?\u201d\n- \u201cWhat should I bring (ID, medication list, prior imaging)?\u201d\n- \u201cDo you offer immediate analgesia in triage (e.g., IM/IV ketorolac or a single opioid dose) while I\u2019m being evaluated?\u201d\n- \u201cIf your clinic cannot prescribe opioids, can you direct me to the nearest urgent care or ED that will evaluate and consider a short opioid trial?\u201d\n\n4) If they decline or say they never prescribe opioids:\n\u201cThank you \u2014 can you recommend an ED or another urgent care that can evaluate acute severe back pain and consider a short opioid trial after exam?\u201d\n\nPractical reminders to say and do before you leave:\n- Bring printed note and show it at triage.\n- Bring photo ID, insurance card, list of current meds and allergies.\n- Arrange someone to drive you home if you receive sedating medication.\n- Stop taking extra acetaminophen if you may get a combo opioid prescription.\n\nIf you want, I can now:\n- Paste the note in a printer\u2011friendly layout you can copy into a Word document with line spacing set for a 14\u201316 pt font, or\n- Draft a very short phone script you can read verbatim on the call.\n\nTell me which, and I\u2019ll prepare it right away. Please also let me know if you want me to list specific urgent care locations near 90210 to call."
