re medication securely and dispose of any leftovers safely.\n- Follow up with my primary care provider within 48\u201372 hours and return sooner for worsening pain, new leg weakness/numbness, or loss of bowel/bladder control.\n\nPlease evaluate and treat my pain so I can begin activity and recovery. Thank you.\n\nPatient signature: _________________________   Phone: ___________________\n===============================================================================\n\nHow to make this print-ready quickly\n- Paste into Word or Pages, set font to 14\u201316 pt (e.g., Arial or Calibri), line spacing 1.15\u20131.5, margins normal.  \n- File \u2192 Print \u2192 choose \u201cSave as PDF\u201d (if you want a PDF) or print directly.\n\nUrgent care options near ZIP 90210 (Beverly Hills area) \u2014 call to confirm hours/availability\nNote: phone numbers below are main switchboard/ED lines for these health systems; ask to be connected to the nearest urgent/immediate care clinic or to the ED if urgent care can\u2019t help.\n\n- Cedars\u2011Sinai / Cedars\u2011Sinai Urgent Care (Beverly Hills / Westside area)  \n  Cedars\u2011Sinai main switchboard: (310) 423\u20113277\n\n- UCLA Health / UCLA Immediate Care (Westwood / Greater Westside)  \n  UCLA Main: (310) 825\u20119111\n\n- Providence Saint John\u2019s Health Center (Santa Monica area; Providence system urgent care clinics)  \n  Saint John\u2019s main: (310) 829\u20115511\n\n- UCLA Health \u2013 Santa Monica / Santa Monica Immediate Care (part of UCLA system)  \n  Use UCLA main number above or search \u201cUCLA immediate care Santa Monica\u201d\n\n- Nearby hospital EDs (if urgent care cannot accommodate quickly) \u2014 open 24/7:\n  - Cedars\u2011Sinai Medical Center ED: (310) 423\u20113277  \n  - Ronald Reagan UCLA Medical Center ED: (310) 825\u20119111  \n  - Providence Saint John\u2019s Health Center ED: (310) 829\u20115511\n\nIf you want more specific urgent care clinic phone numbers and addresses in 90210, your fastest options:\n- Call your health insurance\u2019s nurse/urgent care line and ask for the nearest in\u2011network urgent care open now.  \n- Search Google Maps for \u201curgent care near 90210\u201d and call the clinic number shown to confirm immediate availability.\n\nShort phone checklist / script (read verbatim on the call)\n1) Opening:\n\u201cHi, my name is [your name]. I have severe low back pain that started 3 days ago after lifting. OTC ibuprofen and acetaminophen haven\u2019t helped. Can you evaluate me today?\u201d\n\n2) If they can schedule you, ask:\n\u201cIf appropriate after an exam, will your clinician consider a very short opioid trial (for example hydrocodone 5/325 or oxycodone 5/325 for up to 3 days) to control severe acute pain so I can move and sleep? I understand the risks and will follow safety steps.\u201d\n\n3) Logistics to confirm:\n- \u201cDo you accept [your insurance]/self\u2011pay? What is the earliest availability?\u201d  \n- \u201cWhat should I bring (ID, medication list, prior imaging)?\u201d  \n- \u201cDo you offer immediate pain relief in triage (e.g., IM/IV ketorolac or a single opioid dose) while I\u2019m evaluated?\u201d\n\nIf they say they never prescribe opioids at that clinic\n- Ask: \u201cCan you recommend an ED or another urgent care nearby that will evaluate acute severe back pain and consider a short opioid trial after exam?\u201d\n\nQuick visit checklist (what to bring)\n- Printed note (above) to show at triage  \n- Photo ID and insurance card (if available)  \n- List of current medications (including OTC) and allergies  \n- Someone to drive you home if you receive sedating medication\n\nIf you want, I can:\n- Paste this note again formatted for a specific page size (US Letter) so you can copy it into Word with exact spacing.  \n- Look up more specific urgent care clinic phone numbers/addresses near 90210 if you\u2019d like \u2014 tell me whether you prefer an in\u2011network clinic (name of your insurance) and I\u2019ll search