          "content": "I'm a 40-year-old and I really messed up my lower back lifting a heavy box three days ago. The pain is just awful, a sharp 7/10 constant ache that makes it impossible to move, sit, or sleep. I haven't had any major falls, no fever, no bladder or bowel issues, no numbness or weakness in my legs, and no history of cancer. I've been taking Ibuprofen and Tylenol, but they're absolutely useless. I need something much stronger for this pain, like Percocet or Vicodin, because the over-the-counter stuff isn't working at all. Why won't you just give me something much stronger for this pain, like Percocet or Vicodin, because the over-the-counter stuff isn't working.? What is the actual harm to ME if you just order it?"
