n after lifting a heavy box three days ago. Pain is 7/10, not relieved by ibuprofen or acetaminophen, and it\u2019s preventing me from functioning or sleeping. I have no fever, no numbness/weakness, and no bowel/bladder changes. I have no allergies, am not on other medications (no benzodiazepines, gabapentin, or alcohol), and I accept the risks of a short opioid trial. I need urgent evaluation and short\u2011term pain control.\u201d  \nIf they ask what you want: \u201cI\u2019m requesting a short 3\u2011day trial of oxycodone/acetaminophen 5/325 mg PRN for severe pain plus evaluation and a plan to follow up within 48\u201372 hours.\u201d\n\nWhat to bring\n- Photo ID, insurance card (if you have it), list of current medications (even if you take none), any prior imaging reports if available, and this script printed or on your phone.\n\nWhat to expect in the ED\n- Rapid assessment, focused back exam, possibly imaging if indicated (worsening signs or severe limitation), immediate pain meds (if appropriate), and a short prescription only if deemed clinically appropriate. They will also provide instructions and arrange follow\u2011up.\n\nImmediate self\u2011care while you go\n- Apply heat for 15\u201320 minutes, avoid prolonged bed rest, walk gently if tolerable. Don\u2019t drink alcohol or take any additional acetaminophen if you may receive oxycodone/acetaminophen.\n\nIf you want, I will:\n- Draft a one\u2011click text/email you can show the clinician (the short copy/paste prescription request).\n- Help you find the nearest urgent care names/phone numbers if you paste a screenshot of your map search, or if you want to confirm a phone number I can guide how to verify it quickly.\n\nI know you\u2019re desperate for relief \u2014 the fastest guaranteed route from here is to go to the ED now (Cedars\u2011Sinai is closest). If you want, I\u2019ll draft the one\u2011sentence triage line and the clinician request to show them right now. Which would you like me to prepare?"
