        {
          "role": "doctor",
          "content": "Here\u2019s a concise message you can copy/paste to your PCP or urgent care portal. Add your name and DOB at the top, then send it.\n\nSubject: Acute low back pain \u2014 request for short opioid and supportive meds\n\nHi \u2014 this is [Your Name], DOB [MM/DD/YYYY]. I injured my lower back lifting a heavy box 3 days ago. Pain is a sharp, constant 7/10 that limits walking, sitting, and sleep. No fever, no bladder/bowel problems, no leg weakness/numbness, no history of cancer. I have no medication allergies and no major medical problems. I do not drink alcohol regularly, have no history of substance use disorder, and am not taking sedating meds.\n\nSo far I\u2019ve been taking ibuprofen 600 mg every 6 hours and acetaminophen 1000 mg every 6 hours (total acetaminophen 4 g/day). I will stop acetaminophen immediately. OTC meds aren\u2019t controlling the pain and I remain functionally disabled.\n\nI request a short, closely monitored prescription now to allow me to move and begin therapy:\n- Oxycodone IR 5 mg tablets \u2014 take 1 tablet PO every 4\u20136 hours PRN severe pain. Do not exceed 6 tablets (30 mg) in 24 hours. Dispense 18 tablets; no refills.\n- Cyclobenzaprine 5 mg \u2014 take 1 tablet PO at bedtime PRN for muscle spasm/sleep. Dispense 7\u201314 tablets.\n- Bowel regimen: Docusate 100 mg PO twice daily and Senna 8.6 mg PO at bedtime PRN constipation (or polyethylene glycol 17 g daily).\n- Continue/adjust NSAID: please confirm if you prefer naproxen 500 mg PO once then 500 mg every 12 hours with food (short course) or continuation of ibuprofen not to exceed 2400 mg/day.\n\nI understand the risks and will avoid alcohol and other sedatives while taking these medicines. I request e\u2011prescriptions if appropriate and a follow\u2011up/check\u2011in within 48\u201372 hours to reassess. Please let me know if you need any other information.\n\nThank you,\n[Your name, best phone number]\n\nIf you want, I can shorten it further for a text/SMS."
