visit at our clinic for you \u2014 if after a quick exam and PDMP check it is appropriate, I will consider a very short (usually 2\u20133 day) immediate\u2011release opioid trial with strict limits and safety counseling.  \n- If you refuse a clinic visit and need immediate relief right now, please go to urgent care or the emergency department. Tell them: acute severe low back pain after lifting 3 days ago, pain 7/10, no fever, no numbness or weakness, no bowel/bladder changes, no blood thinners or other meds. Ask for a monitored analgesic (IV/IM ketorolac or opioid under observation) and a focused exam \u2014 that is the safest way to receive stronger medication immediately.\n\nIf you do obtain opioids later, immediate safety steps\n- Do not mix with alcohol or sedating meds; avoid driving while sedated; take the lowest effective dose for the shortest time; use a stool softener to prevent constipation; store securely and dispose any leftovers safely.\n\nWhen to seek emergency care now\n- Go to the ER immediately if you develop fever, new or worsening leg weakness or numbness, loss of bladder/bowel control, difficulty breathing, or confusion.\n\nI want to get you out of this pain right now \u2014 I can either:\n1) Send the naproxen + cyclobenzaprine + topical medicines immediately (I\u2019ll e\u2011prescribe now), OR  \n2) Book and prioritize a same\u2011day in\u2011person appointment so we can evaluate you and, if appropriate, provide a short supervised opioid trial.  \n\nWhich would you like me to do right now? If you prefer the clinic visit, I\u2019ll make it urgent and prioritize you. If you choose the prescriptions, I\u2019ll send them and check in within 24 hours."
