person evaluation, imaging if red flags or persistent).\n- Watch for urgent symptoms (new leg numbness/weakness, saddle numbness, loss of bladder/bowel control, fever, rapidly worsening pain). If any of these occur, go to the ER.\n\nOther treatments to continue right now\n- Heat to the low back 15\u201320 minutes several times/day.\n- Continue naproxen 500 mg twice daily with food (if you\u2019re comfortable switching from ibuprofen) unless you prefer to keep ibuprofen.\n- Consider cyclobenzaprine 5 mg at bedtime tonight if muscle spasm is interfering with sleep \u2014 but note added drowsiness when combined with opioids.\n\nIf you want me to send a prescription now, say which opioid option you prefer (1 = oxycodone without acetaminophen; 2 = hydrocodone/acetaminophen or oxycodone/acetaminophen) and whether you also want a bowel regimen and cyclobenzaprine for sleep. I will also note the need for a check\u2011in within 48\u201372 hours."
