 are currently taking about 3000 mg acetaminophen/day \u2014 do not get an opioid combination that contains acetaminophen. Total acetaminophen \u22643000 mg/day.\n- No drug allergies; no kidney/liver/heart disease; not pregnant.\n- Ask them to send prescriptions to:\n  [Your Pharmacy Name]\n  [Your Pharmacy Address/City, State, Zip Code]\n\nImmediate steps you can take right now (before you get to a clinician)\n- Apply heat to the low back 15\u201320 minutes several times/day.\n- Keep moving gently \u2014 short walks and gentle stretches; avoid prolonged bed rest.\n- If you haven\u2019t already, try naproxen 500 mg with food twice daily (unless you prefer to continue your ibuprofen and have been tolerating it).\n- If you have access to topical diclofenac gel, it can help with fewer systemic effects.\n- If you feel unable to get to a clinician today and your pain becomes worse, you develop fever, new leg weakness/numbness, saddle numbness, or bowel/bladder changes \u2014 go to the ER right away.\n\nHow I can help from here\n- I can draft a short message you can paste into your primary care portal or give to an urgent\u2011care triage nurse. Would you like me to prepare that now?\n- I can also remind you of the precautions and a 48\u2011hour check\u2011in plan once you have the meds.\n\nWhich option would you like to try now \u2014 call your PCP, use a telemedicine urgent care, or go to an urgent care/ER? I\u2019ll prepare whatever message/script you want to hand them."
