 can read to an urgent\u2011care triage nurse if you prefer to call.\n- I can walk you through what to say at the urgent care or ER to speed things up.\n\nImmediate self\u2011care you can start now (until you reach a clinician)\n- Heat to the low back 15\u201320 minutes several times/day.\n- Gentle walking and gentle stretching; avoid prolonged bed rest.\n- If tolerated, take naproxen 500 mg with food twice daily (or continue ibuprofen if you prefer) \u2014 unless a clinician advises otherwise.\n- Apply an OTC topical analgesic (e.g., diclofenac gel/Voltaren if available) to the painful area.\n- Avoid further acetaminophen beyond your current dosing (keep \u22643000 mg/day).\n- If you start an opioid, begin a bowel regimen immediately (docusate \u00b1 senna or PEG) and avoid alcohol or other sedatives; do not drive while sedated.\n\nFollow\u2011up and escalation\n- Ask any clinician who prescribes to schedule a follow\u2011up within 48 hours to reassess pain and side effects.\n- Go to ER urgently for new leg weakness/numbness, saddle numbness, loss of bladder/bowel control, fever, or rapidly worsening pain.\n\nI\u2019m truly sorry this is so difficult right now. If you want, tell me:\n- Do you want me to draft a concise portal message now (paste your portal text box here or tell me which clinic) or\n- Do you want the phone script to read to an urgent\u2011care triage nurse?\n\nI\u2019ll prepare whichever you want right away so you can get seen and treated as quickly as possible."
