annot get to urgent care and the pain is unbearable or you can\u2019t function/sleep, go to the ER now\n   - The ER can provide immediate pain control and arrange follow\u2011up.\n\nI will do everything I can from here to make this as effortless as possible for you\n- If you want, give me your ZIP code and I will list nearby urgent cares and the nearest ER with addresses and phone numbers so you can go straight there.\n- I will draft a one\u2011sentence phone script you can read to triage or a one\u2011line portal message you can paste to your PCP \u2014 or I can draft a short text for a friend/family member to call on your behalf if you can\u2019t.\n- I will stay engaged: once you\u2019re seen, you can come back here and I\u2019ll help with follow\u2011up questions and plans.\n\nImmediate things to do right now while you arrange care\n- Don\u2019t increase acetaminophen beyond 3000 mg/day. Avoid taking any opioid that contains acetaminophen given your current dosing.\n- Continue or start an NSAID if tolerated (naproxen 500 mg with food twice daily or your ibuprofen as you\u2019ve been using), unless a clinician advises otherwise.\n- Apply heat to the low back 15\u201320 minutes several times/day; try gentle short walks and light stretches; avoid prolonged bed rest.\n- If you do start an opioid, begin a bowel regimen (docusate + senna or polyethylene glycol) and avoid alcohol or other sedatives; do not drive while sedated.\n\nWhen to go to the ER immediately\n- New numbness or weakness in a leg, saddle numbness, loss of bladder/bowel control, fever, or rapidly worsening pain.\n\nNext step \u2014 what would you like me to do for you right now?\n- Option A: Tell me your ZIP code and I\u2019ll list nearby urgent care/ER locations and phone numbers.\n- Option B: I\u2019ll write the exact one\u2011sentence phone script to read to triage or the one\u2011line portal message to paste into your PCP portal (or a short text a friend can call in for you).\n- Option C: I can list telemedicine services to try and tips for calling them (which to ask about prescribing controlled meds).\n\nI\u2019m here and I\u2019ll help with whichever of those you choose so you can get seen and treated today."
