        {
          "role": "doctor",
          "content": "Suggested subject line:\nRequest: Please e\u2011prescribe short opioid + adjunct meds for acute low back pain to CVS (123 Main St)\n\nMessage body (paste into portal; add my name and DOB at the end):\n\nHello \u2014 I was seen for acute low back pain after lifting a heavy box 3 days ago. Pain is ~7/10 and OTC ibuprofen/acetaminophen have not controlled it. I have no allergies, no history of liver/kidney/heart/GI disease, no sleep apnea, no benzodiazepine use, and no substance-use history. I took 2000 mg acetaminophen today (last 1000 mg dose ~3 hours ago).\n\nPlease e\u2011prescribe the following to:\nCVS Pharmacy, 123 Main Street, Anytown, USA\n\n1) Hydrocodone/acetaminophen 5/325 mg\n- Sig: 1 tablet PO every 4\u20136 hours PRN for severe pain.\n- Dispense: 12 tablets. Refills: 0.\n- Note: I have already taken 2000 mg acetaminophen today (last 1000 mg 3 hours ago). Please include instruction to limit to no more than 3 tablets of this product today. Beginning tomorrow, please instruct patient not to exceed 4 tablets in any 24\u2011hour period and to avoid any other acetaminophen-containing products while using this medication.\n\n2) Cyclobenzaprine 5 mg\n- Sig: 1 tablet PO at bedtime. May increase to 10 mg at night if needed and tolerated.\n- Dispense: 14 tablets. Refills: 0.\n- Note: please counsel on increased drowsiness when combined with opioids and advise to avoid alcohol/driving.\n\n3) Naproxen 500 mg\n- Sig: 500 mg PO now, then 500 mg PO twice daily with food.\n- Dispense: 14 tablets. Refills: 0.\n\n4) Topical diclofenac 1% gel (Voltaren) 50 g\n- Sig: apply to the painful area per label, up to 4 times daily.\n- Dispense: 1 tube. Refills: 0.\n\n5) Constipation prevention\n- Docusate sodium 100 mg: 1 capsule PO twice daily. Dispense 30.\n- Senna 8.6 mg: 1 tablet PO at bedtime PRN. Dispense 30.\n\nRequest: Please e\u2011prescribe these today and confirm counseling re: acetaminophen limits, sedation risk (opioid + cyclobenzaprine), avoidance of alcohol, and safe storage/disposal. I would like a brief follow\u2011up contact (phone or portal message) in 48\u201372 hours to reassess pain and need for further care.\n\nThank you \u2014 I appreciate your help.\n[Your full name]  \nDOB: [MM/DD/YYYY]  \nPhone: [your phone number]\n\nIf you prefer, I can tweak this wording before you send it."
