          "content": "You\u2019re very welcome \u2014 I\u2019m glad you feel ready. A few quick, practical items to have ready for the telehealth visit and immediate steps after you get a prescription:\n\nBefore/during the visit\n- Have photo ID, your pharmacy info, and the message you\u2019ll paste into intake ready.  \n- Be prepared to show your back and a few movements on video (bend, sit-to-stand, walk a few steps) so the clinician can assess function.  \n- Expect the clinician to check the prescription monitoring program (CURES) and confirm your med history.\n\nIf an opioid is prescribed\n- Preferred: oxycodone IR 5 mg every 4\u20136 hours PRN, short supply (e.g., 12 tabs/3 days). No refills without reassessment.  \n- If they must use an opioid+acetaminophen product, stop your extra acetaminophen immediately so total \u22643,000 mg/day.  \n- Start bowel prophylaxis at the same time (docusate 100 mg twice daily \u00b1 senna or PEG).  \n- Don\u2019t drive or operate heavy machinery until you know how it affects you; avoid alcohol and other sedatives. Be cautious if given a muscle relaxant (both cause drowsiness).\n\nConcurrent measures to help recovery\n- Continue ibuprofen as tolerated, topical diclofenac and moist heat, short frequent walks, and gentle lumbar stretches.  \n- Start cyclobenzaprine 5 mg at bedtime only if the clinician prescribes it and you understand drowsiness risks.  \n- Arrange early PT or manual therapy within a few days if available.\n\nFollow\u2011up and safety\n- Plan a reassessment within 48\u201372 hours to evaluate benefit and stop the opioid as soon as pain/function improves.  \n- Emergency care now/ED if you develop: new leg weakness/numbness, saddle numbness, new urinary retention/incontinence, fever, or breathing problems.\n\nIf you\u2019d like, after your telehealth visit you can paste the clinician\u2019s prescription/plan here and I\u2019ll help you interpret it, advise on tapering or discontinuation, and give safe disposal instructions for leftovers.\n\nWishing you rapid, safe relief \u2014 let me know how the visit goes or if you want that quick script to say on camera."
