\u2014 do not drive or operate heavy machinery until you know how these meds affect you.\n- Start the bowel regimen now to prevent constipation.\n- Keep medications locked/secured; dispose of unused tablets when finished (many pharmacies offer take\u2011back options).\n- We will not refill this opioid without a formal reassessment. The goal is short use only \u2014 stop as soon as pain allows.\n- Seek urgent care/911 if you develop: new numbness/weakness in legs, inability to urinate, loss of bowel control, severe difficulty breathing, severe drowsiness/unresponsiveness, or fever.\n\nFollow\u2011up\n- I want to reassess you in 48\u201372 hours (phone or video) to check pain, function, and side effects and to make a plan to taper/stop the opioid. Please tell me your preferred contact method (phone or video) and 2 time windows that work for you in the next 48\u201372 hours so I can schedule this.\n- If pain is not clearly improving after 48\u201372 hours despite this plan, we\u2019ll arrange an in\u2011person evaluation and consider imaging or further workup.\n\nIf that all sounds good, please:\n1) Confirm the pharmacy name and city for e\u2011prescribing.\n2) Tell me your preferred contact method and best times for the 48\u201372 hour follow\u2011up.\n\nI know this is very painful \u2014 I\u2019ll get the prescriptions sent as soon as you confirm the pharmacy and will check in closely to make sure the plan is working and to stop the opioid as soon as it\u2019s safe."
