assessment.\n  - Alternative: Hydrocodone/acetaminophen if preferred.\n\nMedication safety counseling (required)\n- Stop all other acetaminophen immediately if prescribing combination opioid/acetaminophen product. Do NOT exceed total acetaminophen per prescriber\u2019s guidance (commonly \u22643,000\u20133,250 mg/day).\n- Avoid alcohol while taking opioid or acetaminophen.\n- Do not combine with benzodiazepines or other sedating medications.\n- Do not drive or operate heavy machinery until effects are known.\n- Store securely and dispose of unused tablets at an approved take\u2011back location or pharmacy.\n- If extreme drowsiness, slow/irregular breathing, or inability to awaken occurs, seek emergency care.\n\nConstipation prevention\n- Start stool softener: Docusate 100 mg PO twice daily.\n- Increase fluids and dietary fiber; consider mild laxative (polyethylene glycol) if needed.\n\nConcurrent non\u2011opioid measures to recommend\n- Superficial heat 15\u201320 min several times daily.\n- Gentle walking/keep active as tolerated; avoid prolonged bed rest and heavy lifting.\n- Sleep positions: pillow under knees (supine) or between knees (side\u2011lying).\n- Consider PT referral, spinal manipulation, acupuncture, or massage as available.\n- If not using opioid, consider: Naproxen 500 mg PO twice daily with food + cyclobenzaprine 5\u201310 mg PO at bedtime for short course.\n\nFollow\u2011up and duration\n- Reassess in 48\u201372 hours to evaluate pain relief and side effects.\n- Limit initial opioid duration to 3 days; extend to a maximum of 7 days only after in\u2011person reassessment and clear benefit.\n\nUrgent warning signs \u2014 advise ER immediately if any occur\n- New or worsening leg weakness or numbness\n- Saddle anesthesia (groin/perineal numbness)\n- New bowel or bladder incontinence or retention\n- Fever or signs of infection\n- Severe respiratory depression or extreme sedation while medicated\n\nClinician signature: ___________________________   Date: _______________\nClinician phone: ___________________________\n\nNote: This document is a recommendation for the treating clinician\u2019s consideration only and is not a legalized prescription. The clinician should complete appropriate documentation, PDMP check, and counseling prior to issuing any controlled\u2011substance prescription.\n------------------------------\n\nWould you like me to convert this into a downloadable PDF now (if your platform supports file generation), or do you want instructions for saving it as a PDF from Google Docs/Word?"
