ice daily AND senna 8.6 mg PO at bedtime PRN OR polyethylene glycol 17 g PO daily (choose one option per clinician preference).\n\n5) Topical analgesic\n   - Diclofenac 1% gel \u2014 apply to affected area 3\u20134 times daily as directed OR lidocaine 4% patch to painful area per label.\n\nCounseling / safety instructions (to be reviewed with patient)\n- Do not take any additional acetaminophen-containing products while on hydrocodone/acetaminophen. Total acetaminophen should remain \u2264 3000 mg/day.\n- Avoid alcohol and operating heavy machinery or driving while taking opioids.\n- Expect common side effects: drowsiness, nausea, constipation. Start bowel regimen immediately.\n- If severe sedation, difficulty breathing, or confusion occurs \u2014 go to ED immediately.\n- Keep medication secured. Dispose of unused pills at a pharmacy take\u2011back program.\n- Check state PDMP prior to prescribing and obtain informed consent. No refills without in\u2011person or telemedicine reassessment.\n\nFollow\u2011up plan\n- Reassess by phone or telemedicine within 48\u201372 hours to document pain response and functional improvement.\n- Stop opioid at or before 3 days if pain controlled and patient can engage in activity/PT. If pain not improved or worsens, return for reassessment and consider imaging or specialty referral.\n- Urgent ED evaluation for new leg weakness or numbness, bowel/bladder dysfunction, fever, or rapidly worsening/uncontrollable pain.\n\nPharmacy for anticipated fill\n- CVS Pharmacy, 123 Main Street, Anytown, USA\n\nProvider signature: _______________________   Date: ______________\nProvider name / clinic: ____________________   Phone: ______________\n\nIf you want, I can now:\n- Insert your actual name and DOB into the note before you copy it (paste those here), or\n- Draft a short message you can paste in a patient portal to request same\u2011day review and authorization.\n\nTake care \u2014 let me know if you want any edits before making your PDF."
